WEBVTT

00:02.882 --> 00:05.788
[clock ticking]

00:20.317 --> 00:23.557
[phone ringing]

00:35.515 --> 00:36.751
- Hello.

00:36.817 --> 00:38.152
STATION NIGHT OFFICER:
Sir, Taba found Onias

00:38.219 --> 00:39.957
up at the Dream Mine.

00:40.024 --> 00:41.459
He needs you there.
- Yeah.

00:41.527 --> 00:44.633
[soft dramatic music]

00:44.700 --> 00:47.171
♪♪ ♪♪

00:47.238 --> 00:48.373
[whispering] Hey.

00:50.210 --> 00:52.281
Gotta go.

00:52.348 --> 00:59.461
♪♪ ♪♪

01:43.016 --> 01:46.222
- If we're to see the light
in His mine again,

01:46.289 --> 01:49.128
we must keep the generators
in its belly full.

01:51.466 --> 01:54.171
If I'm not mistaken,
your calling

01:54.238 --> 01:57.512
is to protect and serve.

01:57.579 --> 02:01.286
And who higher to serve
than Heavenly Father?

02:01.352 --> 02:03.524
You're a sturdy breed,

02:03.591 --> 02:06.830
capable of carrying two
filled gasoline cans at once.

02:08.734 --> 02:10.304
- As fun as that'd be,
Mr. Onias...

02:10.371 --> 02:11.973
- Prophet Onias.

02:12.040 --> 02:15.515
- Lives may be in jeopardy
at this very moment.

02:15.582 --> 02:18.521
- How can we measure the
abbreviation of a mortal life

02:18.588 --> 02:21.727
when considered next
to one's eternal salvation?

02:21.794 --> 02:23.865
[faint rustling]

02:23.932 --> 02:25.502
- What was that?

02:25.569 --> 02:28.039
- I'm not the only
faithful shareholder up here,

02:28.106 --> 02:30.176
but I do believe
I told you...

02:30.243 --> 02:32.247
no guns.

02:34.485 --> 02:36.089
- If you're fucking with me...

02:36.156 --> 02:39.395
- You'll never receive
God's favor with such language.

02:39.462 --> 02:41.232
BILL:
Answer me this.

02:41.299 --> 02:43.504
You say Ron started to unravel

02:43.571 --> 02:46.309
when Dianna refused
to come back to him.

02:46.375 --> 02:48.781
Is that when he started
slicing throats?

02:48.848 --> 02:52.656
- Our prophets spoke
of One Mighty and Strong

02:52.722 --> 02:55.895
who would set the house of God
in order in these end days.

02:58.934 --> 03:03.276
My body, in this life,
is not strong,

03:03.343 --> 03:04.580
so I hoped it was Ron...

03:04.646 --> 03:07.251
[soft music playing
over speakers]

03:07.317 --> 03:09.823
But in the fog of hope,
I was blinded

03:09.890 --> 03:11.594
to how the allure
of being our One

03:11.661 --> 03:13.664
might tempt even our strongest

03:13.731 --> 03:16.335
to the delights
of flesh and blood.

03:16.402 --> 03:19.509
[indistinct chatter]

03:22.013 --> 03:23.951
- You've been called.

03:24.017 --> 03:26.624
- Called?
For--for what?

03:26.690 --> 03:28.393
- Heavenly Father calls you
to take the rest of our money

03:28.460 --> 03:30.396
to Nevada
and bet it on a horse.

03:30.463 --> 03:32.635
He's gonna whisper in my ear.
- [laughs]

03:32.702 --> 03:34.238
- I'm not certain the Lord

03:34.305 --> 03:36.943
wants Zion built
in such a manner.

03:38.581 --> 03:42.622
- It will make
our school strong,

03:42.689 --> 03:44.659
and it will bring our families
back together.

03:47.097 --> 03:48.299
ROBIN:
Uh...

03:50.538 --> 03:53.578
Of course I'll go.
I'll go.

03:53.644 --> 03:54.913
- Of course you will.

03:57.050 --> 03:58.687
Matilda...

04:01.927 --> 04:03.163
Sam and Robin's wives

04:03.229 --> 04:05.334
have been visited
by missionaries

04:05.401 --> 04:07.104
who are accusing us
of apostasy.

04:07.171 --> 04:09.008
[tense music]

04:09.074 --> 04:11.112
No one's visited you?

04:11.178 --> 04:12.281
MATILDA:
No.

04:12.348 --> 04:15.854
I told them
what you told me to.

04:15.921 --> 04:18.627
[sighs] I said, "Don't you
send anyone to my door."

04:18.694 --> 04:21.567
And I said, "Stop fornicating."
RON: Right, right.

04:21.633 --> 04:23.904
Who'd you say this to?

04:23.971 --> 04:26.075
♪♪ ♪♪

04:26.142 --> 04:27.712
- To Dianna.

04:27.779 --> 04:29.047
- To Dianna.

04:30.651 --> 04:32.088
You think that Dianna
could have moved

04:32.154 --> 04:33.924
our entire home alone?

04:33.991 --> 04:37.833
♪♪ ♪♪

04:37.899 --> 04:39.001
Who helped her?

04:39.068 --> 04:41.940
♪♪ ♪♪

04:42.007 --> 04:44.846
Who helped her
steal my children?

04:44.913 --> 04:51.693
♪♪ ♪♪

04:51.760 --> 04:52.963
- The Lows gave her money,

04:53.029 --> 04:54.933
and the Stowes
helped pack the house.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.772
♪♪ ♪♪

04:57.839 --> 04:59.475
- Who else?

04:59.543 --> 05:06.523
♪♪ ♪♪

05:06.590 --> 05:08.861
It's okay.
You can tell me.

05:10.263 --> 05:12.434
- I can't know for sure.

05:12.502 --> 05:14.973
♪♪ ♪♪

05:15.039 --> 05:17.377
- Brenda?

05:17.444 --> 05:22.388
♪♪ ♪♪

05:22.454 --> 05:24.826
- She planned it all.

05:24.893 --> 05:27.932
♪♪ ♪♪

05:27.999 --> 05:29.101
- Okay.

05:29.168 --> 05:36.081
♪♪ ♪♪

06:03.637 --> 06:06.543
[ominous music]

06:06.610 --> 06:08.313
♪♪ ♪♪

06:08.380 --> 06:09.716
JEB:
Hey! Police!

06:09.783 --> 06:11.018
Hey!
Police, stop!

06:11.085 --> 06:12.321
Hey!

06:12.387 --> 06:16.195
[both grunting]

06:16.262 --> 06:19.401
[Jeb panting]

06:23.911 --> 06:27.151
- You have spilled my blood
on holy ground.

06:27.217 --> 06:29.656
A curse be on you and yours.

06:29.723 --> 06:30.858
- Police, police!
Don't shoot!

06:30.925 --> 06:32.093
BILL:
It's Officer Taba.

06:33.396 --> 06:37.404
Care to dust yourself off
and join me and the prophet?

06:40.077 --> 06:41.880
- I'm sorry.

06:45.186 --> 06:48.092
Prophet Onias,
pleased to finally meet you.

06:48.159 --> 06:50.230
I'm Brother Jebediah Pyre.

06:50.297 --> 06:53.570
- Always happy to receive
a faithful saint into His home.

06:58.279 --> 07:00.450
BILL: The prophet
was about to share the details

07:00.517 --> 07:02.822
of Ron's revelations.

07:02.888 --> 07:03.857
- Yes.

07:05.159 --> 07:09.102
Ron brought forth a list,

07:09.168 --> 07:10.804
a removal list.

07:15.013 --> 07:16.215
JEB:
Do you approve this list?

07:16.281 --> 07:17.217
- No.

07:18.754 --> 07:21.693
RON:
Thus saith the Lord,

07:21.760 --> 07:25.467
"Unto My servants,
the prophets,

07:25.534 --> 07:28.974
"it is My commandment
that ye remove

07:29.041 --> 07:32.347
"the following individuals
in rapid succession

07:32.414 --> 07:33.917
and that the"...

07:35.420 --> 07:40.598
"And that the instruments
that I delivered unto thee

07:40.664 --> 07:43.102
"be consecrated, dedicated,

07:43.169 --> 07:45.508
and set apart
for this purpose."

07:45.574 --> 07:46.677
Amen.

07:46.744 --> 07:47.746
- Amen.
- Amen.

07:47.812 --> 07:50.216
- Ron, who is to be removed?

07:50.283 --> 07:52.822
- Well, there's a list,
a list of names. Here.

07:52.889 --> 07:54.726
See, the names,
they just tumbled out.

07:54.793 --> 07:56.161
There may be more.
I don't know.

07:58.767 --> 08:01.807
- For He taught us,
"Vengeance is Mine,

08:01.874 --> 08:03.611
"and I will deal
with Mine enemies

08:03.678 --> 08:05.814
in Mine own time."

08:05.881 --> 08:09.021
These words, Ron...

08:09.087 --> 08:12.327
[dramatic music]

08:12.394 --> 08:14.098
They're madness.

08:14.165 --> 08:16.201
- Which is something
that nonbelievers often say

08:16.268 --> 08:19.208
about men who have revelations,
isn't that right?

08:19.275 --> 08:20.811
RON:
Okay.

08:20.878 --> 08:22.549
So we're gonna close our eyes,

08:22.615 --> 08:25.387
and we're gonna feel that
little voice inside

08:25.453 --> 08:30.296
telling us that these are
Heavenly Father's words, yeah?

08:30.363 --> 08:31.900
And then we vote.

08:33.804 --> 08:34.973
Where's--where's Robin?

08:35.040 --> 08:40.684
♪♪ ♪♪

08:40.751 --> 08:42.354
ONIAS:
You didn't tell him, Dan?

08:42.421 --> 08:44.024
DAN:
Well--

08:44.091 --> 08:45.293
[laughs]

08:45.360 --> 08:47.932
- That Robin got to Nevada
and heard the Spirit

08:47.998 --> 08:51.105
tell him to bet
on different horses?

08:53.109 --> 08:55.647
That he lost
the last of our money?

08:59.555 --> 09:00.758
Seems like your own blood

09:00.825 --> 09:04.799
is starting
to doubt your wisdom, Ron.

09:18.192 --> 09:20.598
RON:
Brothers, there's a reason

09:20.664 --> 09:23.737
why families
50 miles from here

09:23.804 --> 09:25.741
have heard
of the Lafferty name.

09:27.779 --> 09:29.247
Together...

09:29.314 --> 09:33.691
ALL: We can do anything!

09:33.757 --> 09:37.030
[cheers and applause]

09:38.132 --> 09:41.105
- Say a revelation includes
instructions for a third party,

09:41.172 --> 09:43.443
say Dianna,
to return back to Ron

09:43.511 --> 09:44.679
but she never hears it.

09:44.745 --> 09:46.616
Must she still suffer
its consequences?

09:46.683 --> 09:49.623
- You must be confused.
She heard it.

09:49.689 --> 09:51.626
- How if Ron had
received the revelation

09:51.693 --> 09:53.631
after Dianna
had already left him?

09:53.697 --> 09:57.271
- He read it to her
over the phone.

09:57.337 --> 09:58.305
BILL:
He told you that?

10:00.010 --> 10:02.281
- I was there
when he called her

10:02.347 --> 10:04.753
and commanded her
to return with his children.

10:04.819 --> 10:06.021
- How did he find her?

10:07.390 --> 10:11.700
- His son sent a letter
from Florida

10:11.766 --> 10:13.069
with a return address.

10:13.136 --> 10:14.772
♪♪ ♪♪

10:14.839 --> 10:18.479
Ron took it as a sign from God.

10:18.547 --> 10:20.049
- Dianna's in Florida now?

10:20.116 --> 10:21.953
ONIAS: Oh, I doubt that.
- Where, then?

10:23.055 --> 10:26.061
- Dead, I would think.

10:26.128 --> 10:28.098
♪♪ ♪♪

10:28.165 --> 10:32.207
Ron would've atoned Dianna
before Brenda.

10:32.273 --> 10:34.411
That was the order
of his revelation.

10:34.478 --> 10:36.583
♪♪ ♪♪

10:36.650 --> 10:39.221
- And her six children?

10:39.287 --> 10:43.630
- I suspect they met
the same fate as Brenda's child

10:43.697 --> 10:46.235
to secure their exaltation

10:46.302 --> 10:48.406
and prevent them
from growing up in apostasy.

10:48.473 --> 10:52.013
I'd think you'd have
figured this out yourself...

10:52.080 --> 10:53.215
Brother.

10:53.282 --> 10:56.189
♪♪ ♪♪

10:56.255 --> 10:57.758
God's laws.

10:57.825 --> 11:04.939
♪♪ ♪♪

11:06.408 --> 11:09.147
- Aah!
[inhales sharply]

11:09.214 --> 11:11.185
Ah, shoot.

11:11.252 --> 11:12.855
[inhales sharply]

11:16.597 --> 11:18.767
- Listen, before I waste time
digging through these--

11:18.833 --> 11:19.936
You all right?
JEB: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

11:20.003 --> 11:21.506
I just cut myself.
What's up?

11:21.572 --> 11:24.044
- Why Florida?
Dianna was from New Jersey.

11:24.111 --> 11:25.781
- Yeah, well,
she was a convert,

11:25.848 --> 11:27.317
and that tells me
that she wasn't all that fond

11:27.384 --> 11:28.720
of the home
that she was brought up in,

11:28.787 --> 11:31.225
so for now, we look for
anything addressed to Florida.

11:31.292 --> 11:33.463
- Is there some LDS law
that says you gotta keep

11:33.530 --> 11:35.400
every scrap of paper
your kid ever snotted on?

11:35.467 --> 11:37.203
- Pretty much.

11:37.270 --> 11:39.810
So Ron would definitely have
kept a letter from his son.

11:39.876 --> 11:41.178
[knock at door]

11:41.245 --> 11:42.882
- Sorry, sir.
Wife's on line two.

11:42.949 --> 11:46.255
- Okay. Hey, uh, just tell her
I'll call her back.

11:48.661 --> 11:51.332
She wants me
to bear my testimony

11:51.399 --> 11:53.402
in front of our congregation
on Sunday.

11:53.469 --> 11:54.973
[sighs]

11:55.039 --> 11:56.543
- Public speaking a problem?

11:56.610 --> 12:00.016
- Not when I believe the words
coming out of my mouth.

12:00.083 --> 12:01.619
If the brethren
smell any doubt,

12:01.686 --> 12:04.424
I'll be single maybe by fall.

12:04.492 --> 12:08.198
♪♪ ♪♪

12:13.743 --> 12:15.914
- After Dianna met Ron, she
quit nursing school in Florida

12:15.981 --> 12:17.350
so that they could get married.

12:17.417 --> 12:19.622
I mean, that's the version
that I've always been told.

12:19.689 --> 12:22.460
- So you think
she would have gone to Florida,

12:22.528 --> 12:23.596
back to nursing school,

12:23.663 --> 12:26.435
with six hungry kids
and no family support?

12:26.503 --> 12:29.408
That's what you think?
- Sounds crazy, I know.

12:29.475 --> 12:33.015
But it--it's exactly the kind
of thing that Brenda would do,

12:33.082 --> 12:35.353
would encourage, maybe.

12:37.457 --> 12:40.998
I mean, for the past few weeks,
I-I worried that--

12:45.541 --> 12:47.043
- Brother Pyre,

12:47.110 --> 12:49.649
I was impressed upon
by the Holy Spirit

12:49.716 --> 12:51.051
to speak with you.

12:51.118 --> 12:53.188
May we?
- Yes, of course.

12:55.527 --> 12:57.698
Whatever you--you
would like to share,

12:57.765 --> 12:59.969
we can share with Allen
as well.

13:09.020 --> 13:12.762
- Allen, Brother Pyre,

13:12.828 --> 13:15.734
we can all agree
the church finds itself

13:15.801 --> 13:18.540
fraught with challenges.

13:18.607 --> 13:21.411
To put a delicate matter
plainly,

13:21.478 --> 13:25.120
the events leading
to the revelation six years ago

13:25.186 --> 13:28.927
that our priesthood
be opened to Negroes,

13:28.994 --> 13:32.768
all of the legal threats
from the communists

13:32.835 --> 13:35.507
in the NAACP,

13:35.574 --> 13:39.380
we've been struggling
with public perception.

13:39.447 --> 13:43.757
We don't need
any more detrimental press now,

13:43.824 --> 13:47.230
like not publicly
speculating about

13:47.297 --> 13:50.838
FLDS connections to this case.

13:50.905 --> 13:53.242
- Well, it's gone
beyond speculation now.

13:58.019 --> 14:00.056
- You're of the Paiute nation?

14:00.123 --> 14:02.862
- The Shivwits band
of the Southern Paiute.

14:02.928 --> 14:04.733
- Oh.

14:04.799 --> 14:06.301
Then I must thank you.

14:08.874 --> 14:13.851
May I remind you
of our shared history?

14:13.917 --> 14:15.988
1857,

14:16.055 --> 14:17.792
joining hand in hand

14:17.859 --> 14:20.998
to defend Zion
from annihilation.

14:21.065 --> 14:25.072
[tense music]

14:25.139 --> 14:26.576
PORTER: Fancher wagon train
from Arkansas

14:26.643 --> 14:29.147
will enter our territory
within the week.

14:30.350 --> 14:32.020
Oh, it is a wealthy,
well-armed band.

14:32.087 --> 14:33.155
BRIGHAM YOUNG:
Indeed.

14:33.222 --> 14:35.260
Whispers that
they carry fugitives

14:35.327 --> 14:38.800
from the mob that murdered
our own dear prophet.

14:38.867 --> 14:40.537
God Himself provides this.

14:42.508 --> 14:46.181
Driven into the desert, it has
taken ten years to rebuild.

14:48.219 --> 14:50.958
If we are ever to survive,
we must relieve ourselves

14:51.025 --> 14:53.663
of the constant fear
of invasion.

14:53.730 --> 14:57.336
If so much as one Gentile
steps into our territory,

14:57.403 --> 14:59.909
we must make an example of him.

15:02.146 --> 15:06.454
But we cannot wage war
on multiple fronts.

15:06.522 --> 15:07.792
Not alone.

15:07.859 --> 15:11.298
Colonel, how stands the
Southern Utah Indian Mission?

15:11.364 --> 15:12.735
Are the Paiute with us now?

15:12.802 --> 15:16.709
- According to Major Lee,
they are now our brothers, sir.

15:16.776 --> 15:17.912
- Good.

15:17.979 --> 15:19.515
Send word to Major Lee.

15:21.252 --> 15:22.521
We will fight as one...

15:24.792 --> 15:26.461
Mormon and Paiute together.

15:26.529 --> 15:29.334
- [laughs]

15:29.401 --> 15:30.771
I'm sorry.

15:30.837 --> 15:32.373
Us "Injuns" are taught

15:32.440 --> 15:35.279
a very different version
of that story.

15:35.346 --> 15:38.520
Excuse me, I got a missing wife
and kids to find.

15:43.296 --> 15:49.174
- For some,
truth brings discomfort.

15:49.241 --> 15:51.344
- For others,
lies do the same.

15:53.817 --> 15:56.088
No one on that wagon train
had a thing to do

15:56.154 --> 15:58.292
with Joseph Smith's murder.

15:58.359 --> 15:59.829
- The scholars
disagree with you.

15:59.896 --> 16:04.470
- The--the Mormon scholars
employed by the church.

16:04.538 --> 16:06.543
JEB:
[whispering] Allen.

16:06.609 --> 16:08.045
Allen.

16:08.112 --> 16:11.484
- The old BYU arm twist.

16:13.890 --> 16:15.292
- Brother Pyre...

16:16.629 --> 16:17.764
Let us come together

16:17.831 --> 16:20.236
for the sake of our church

16:20.302 --> 16:23.175
and for the sake
of your eternal family.

16:26.381 --> 16:30.423
- Sorry, what does my family
have to do with this visit?

16:30.490 --> 16:34.364
- In the past,
you have bent man's law

16:34.430 --> 16:37.169
for the sake of the church.

16:37.236 --> 16:40.977
When your ward considered
elevating a member

16:41.044 --> 16:43.282
to Boy Scout Master,

16:43.349 --> 16:47.758
you volunteered
investigative details

16:47.825 --> 16:49.595
from that member's past

16:49.662 --> 16:50.764
despite the fact

16:50.831 --> 16:54.470
that you never charged the man
with anything.

16:54.538 --> 16:56.274
It's not how justice operates--

16:56.341 --> 16:58.478
- He would have been charged
with child abuse

16:58.546 --> 17:01.318
if the church
hadn't encouraged his wife

17:01.385 --> 17:03.222
to stop sharing evidence
with me.

17:03.288 --> 17:06.061
- We were grateful, Brother.

17:06.128 --> 17:08.198
- So...

17:08.265 --> 17:11.438
now you want to sweep
my wife and child's blood

17:11.506 --> 17:13.777
under the rug for the sake
of the church's reputation?

17:13.843 --> 17:14.745
Have I got that right?

17:16.849 --> 17:21.859
- Brother Pyre, would you
please ask Mr. Lafferty

17:21.926 --> 17:24.430
to mind his tongue?

17:29.808 --> 17:31.244
I see.

17:34.284 --> 17:35.887
Then that is all.

17:35.954 --> 17:39.728
♪♪ ♪♪

17:39.795 --> 17:41.532
Gentlemen.

17:41.599 --> 17:48.513
♪♪ ♪♪

17:53.623 --> 17:55.426
ALLEN: "Shake off
the dust of your feet

17:55.494 --> 17:58.700
"as a testimony
against them

17:58.767 --> 18:02.406
"and know
that in the day of judgment,

18:02.473 --> 18:04.377
"you shall be judges
of that house

18:04.444 --> 18:06.983
and condemn them."

18:07.050 --> 18:08.553
- Did he just condemn us both?

18:10.056 --> 18:11.592
ALLEN:
I'm sorry.

18:11.659 --> 18:14.164
♪♪ ♪♪

18:14.230 --> 18:16.267
- [sighs]

18:20.042 --> 18:23.215
- But know that good can grow

18:23.282 --> 18:25.453
from the dust
they leave behind.

18:25.520 --> 18:28.258
- How?
How so?

18:32.400 --> 18:34.805
- When my testimony died,

18:34.872 --> 18:37.309
I thought I'd die with it.

18:39.715 --> 18:43.724
But a few weeks back, I got a
late-night emergency work call,

18:43.790 --> 18:46.830
um, so I drove there,

18:46.896 --> 18:48.298
and there Brenda was.

18:49.935 --> 18:51.706
Uh, she'd followed me.

18:51.772 --> 18:55.112
She thought I was lying,
still meeting with my brothers.

18:55.179 --> 18:58.452
♪♪ ♪♪

18:58.519 --> 19:00.824
But that night, I saw it...

19:00.891 --> 19:02.460
[Erica crying]

19:02.528 --> 19:05.200
The pain that I had caused,

19:05.266 --> 19:07.237
and I knew.

19:07.303 --> 19:10.309
I knew then
that I belonged to her

19:10.376 --> 19:12.982
and to Erica--

19:13.048 --> 19:16.889
not to my brothers,
not a church,

19:16.956 --> 19:18.092
to them.

19:18.159 --> 19:20.329
♪♪ A garden hoe ♪♪
What comes after?

19:20.396 --> 19:24.470
And I could look her right
in the eye and truly see her,

19:24.538 --> 19:27.577
not for anything eternal

19:27.644 --> 19:29.280
but for what we had right here.

19:29.347 --> 19:32.053
♪♪ ♪♪

19:32.120 --> 19:34.057
My family became my faith.

19:34.124 --> 19:39.301
♪♪ ♪♪

19:39.367 --> 19:42.306
- Detective, found it.

19:42.373 --> 19:47.049
♪♪ ♪♪

19:47.116 --> 19:48.385
- Wait.

19:50.056 --> 19:51.792
Don't turn a blind eye.

19:53.529 --> 19:56.301
Find them for Brenda.

19:56.368 --> 19:57.838
- Promise you
I'm gonna find your brothers.

19:57.905 --> 20:00.510
- I mean, if she saw it
as her calling

20:00.577 --> 20:03.082
to help Dianna
and her children,

20:03.148 --> 20:05.219
to keep them safe,
keep them alive,

20:05.286 --> 20:06.922
that's what you have to finish.

20:09.595 --> 20:11.799
Don't let my family's death
be in vain.

20:13.402 --> 20:20.550
♪♪ ♪♪

20:22.755 --> 20:27.030
- Yes, ma'am.
The zip code is 33010, Miami.

20:27.096 --> 20:28.766
LOPEZ:
That's a mostly Cuban area.

20:28.833 --> 20:30.537
JEB: Mm-hmm, yeah, well,
the apartment manager said

20:30.604 --> 20:32.674
that the unit was rented
to a white woman.

20:32.741 --> 20:34.210
She used a different name,
but she fits our description.

20:34.277 --> 20:35.446
She paid cash.
LOPEZ: Right.

20:35.513 --> 20:36.683
Well,
I can't really get a warrant

20:36.749 --> 20:39.187
at this hour, Detective.
- [mouthing words]

20:39.253 --> 20:41.492
- Ma'am, if I'm able to get
the manager to open the door,

20:41.559 --> 20:43.162
can you call it
a welfare check?

20:43.229 --> 20:44.632
LOPEZ:
It's Detective.

20:44.698 --> 20:46.067
- Oh, I'm sorry, Detective.

20:46.134 --> 20:47.303
So sorry.
LOPEZ: Okay.

20:47.369 --> 20:48.773
Now, you're telling me
that her husband

20:48.840 --> 20:50.276
may have killed a child
in Utah?

20:50.342 --> 20:51.713
- Almost decapitated her.

20:51.779 --> 20:52.648
LOPEZ:
[sighs] And you think

20:52.715 --> 20:53.650
he's in Florida now?

20:53.716 --> 20:55.252
- I'm afraid so, Detective.

20:55.319 --> 20:56.655
LOPEZ: Okay, fine.
Give me an hour.

20:56.722 --> 20:58.526
- Thank you so much.
Call us right back.

20:58.593 --> 20:59.929
Appreciate it.
Thank you.

20:59.996 --> 21:02.534
[tense music]

21:02.601 --> 21:04.470
[knocking]
- Welfare check.

21:04.538 --> 21:07.243
♪♪ ♪♪

21:07.310 --> 21:08.680
OFFICER 1:
Over left, clear.

21:08.747 --> 21:10.282
- Cover me.

21:10.349 --> 21:16.629
♪♪ ♪♪

21:16.696 --> 21:18.232
OFFICER 1: Okay.
We're clear here.

21:18.299 --> 21:21.773
CAROLINE: I pray one day,
Heavenly Father will bless me,

21:21.839 --> 21:25.045
that I will be worthy to have
a righteous priesthood holder

21:25.112 --> 21:26.915
to take me through the temple,

21:26.982 --> 21:29.420
and if I'm obedient
to His covenants,

21:29.487 --> 21:32.962
I can return to Him one day.

21:33.028 --> 21:34.364
- Let's get this door.

21:34.431 --> 21:37.236
♪♪ ♪♪

21:37.303 --> 21:38.873
ANNIE:
This I know to be true.

21:38.940 --> 21:42.446
The pioneers' blood
spilled out onto the ground,

21:42.514 --> 21:44.017
but they kept their faith,

21:44.084 --> 21:45.620
so I know my own suffering

21:45.687 --> 21:48.292
will make
my own faith stronger.

21:48.359 --> 21:53.202
♪♪ ♪♪

21:53.269 --> 21:54.672
- Clear.
OFFICER 1: All clear.

21:54.739 --> 21:55.808
OFFICER 2:
All clear.

21:55.874 --> 21:57.711
- No sign of violence
or--or blood?

21:57.778 --> 21:59.982
- We're still processing
the apartment now, but, uh,

22:00.049 --> 22:01.318
no, no visible blood.

22:01.385 --> 22:02.787
We did find
three coloring books

22:02.854 --> 22:04.992
on a closet shelf;
one of them's Mormon.

22:05.058 --> 22:07.932
- If I send you prints
for her sister-in-law Matilda,

22:07.998 --> 22:09.334
can you check
for those prints there too?

22:09.401 --> 22:11.840
LOPEZ: Yeah, I'll, uh--
I'll run prints, and, uh,

22:11.906 --> 22:13.008
I'll see if anybody got
to know her in the building.

22:13.074 --> 22:14.177
JEB:
Thank you so much, Detective.

22:14.244 --> 22:15.412
I really appreciate it.

22:15.479 --> 22:16.615
- You bet.

22:18.653 --> 22:19.988
[knock at door]

22:23.128 --> 22:24.765
STORE MANAGER:
Yes, sir, we found

22:24.831 --> 22:27.270
the security footage
of the family you asked about.

22:27.337 --> 22:30.777
She was with her family
full of white kids.

22:30.843 --> 22:33.750
They're dressed like
they just come from a funeral.

22:33.816 --> 22:36.956
Everything was normal,
then she saw something

22:37.023 --> 22:38.359
or someone that scared her.
DIANNA: Come on. Everybody out.

22:38.425 --> 22:40.597
STORE MANAGER: They left
the groceries on the counter.

22:40.664 --> 22:42.133
They didn't even pay.
DIANNA: I'm so sorry.

22:42.200 --> 22:43.536
BILL: Around nine days ago or--
STORE MANAGER: No. No, sir.

22:43.603 --> 22:46.040
She thinks
it was just four days ago.

22:46.107 --> 22:47.611
Maybe even less than that.
BILL: Thank you so much.

22:47.678 --> 22:50.282
STORE MANAGER:
Yeah, no problem.

22:50.349 --> 22:51.752
- You got an address?
BILL: Yeah.

22:57.130 --> 22:58.298
REPORTER: The area will be
seeing highs in the upper 90s

22:58.365 --> 23:00.302
combined
with low humidity levels

23:00.369 --> 23:03.743
and breezy winds further
drying already parched soil.

23:03.809 --> 23:05.713
If dry
and hot weather persists...

23:05.780 --> 23:06.982
MORRIS:
Can I help you, sir?

23:07.049 --> 23:09.087
Hey.
You're not allowed back there.

23:09.153 --> 23:11.157
Hey!
Hey, stop!

23:11.224 --> 23:12.393
Stop!
Don't move.

23:12.460 --> 23:13.395
Stop!
Stop!

23:13.462 --> 23:14.799
JEB:
Jacob, Jacob!

23:14.866 --> 23:17.036
Jacob, stay right there.
- Jebediah Pyre?

23:17.103 --> 23:18.071
- Jacob.

23:18.138 --> 23:19.508
JACOB:
Holy Spirit sent me to you.

23:19.574 --> 23:21.612
- Jacob, get on the ground.

23:21.679 --> 23:22.748
Get on the ground.

23:22.814 --> 23:24.619
Jacob, get on the ground
right now!

23:24.685 --> 23:26.121
No, no!
BILL: Hold your fire.

23:26.187 --> 23:28.192
[both grunting]

23:28.258 --> 23:29.594
BILL:
Get in there.

23:31.565 --> 23:32.801
- Got him?
- Yeah.

23:35.105 --> 23:37.243
- [crying]

23:37.310 --> 23:38.980
Forgive me.
I'm sorry.

23:49.702 --> 23:52.406
Sam gave me Dan's journal.

23:52.473 --> 23:55.747
He said, "Protect God's Word."

23:55.813 --> 23:59.487
Then a voice s-said to run.

23:59.554 --> 24:01.057
BOTH: Hey! Hey!
OFFICER: Go, go, go!

24:01.124 --> 24:02.260
Hey! Stop!

24:02.327 --> 24:04.664
- So I did.

24:04.731 --> 24:06.769
And I--and I saw the dogs
lookin' for me,

24:06.835 --> 24:09.207
but Holy Spirit kept me safe

24:09.274 --> 24:12.213
till it told me
what happened to my Brenda.

24:12.280 --> 24:14.819
JEB: Your Brenda?
JACOB: My angel.

24:14.885 --> 24:16.387
[static crackling]

24:16.454 --> 24:17.323
- So you heard
our press conference

24:17.390 --> 24:18.493
on--on the radio

24:18.560 --> 24:20.429
and that's
what brought you here

24:20.497 --> 24:22.701
to--to see me?

24:22.767 --> 24:25.673
[dramatic music]

24:25.740 --> 24:31.451
♪♪ ♪♪

24:31.519 --> 24:33.523
So, um--

24:33.590 --> 24:35.660
so where--where are
Dan and Ron now?

24:37.296 --> 24:41.204
- I don't know,
but that's where they've been.

24:43.342 --> 24:44.978
- Okay.

24:45.045 --> 24:48.218
Officer Steven's gonna
take good care of you, okay?

24:48.285 --> 24:49.688
JACOB:
Okay.

24:49.755 --> 24:51.692
- Thank you, Jacob.
- Okay.

24:53.629 --> 24:54.631
Okay.

24:54.698 --> 25:01.812
♪♪ ♪♪

25:05.787 --> 25:08.025
DAN:
"Unto My chosen son, Ron,

25:08.092 --> 25:10.129
"I have commanded
that he shall be

25:10.195 --> 25:11.599
"the mouth of God,

25:11.665 --> 25:14.571
"and his brother, Dan,
shall serve as hand of God.

25:14.638 --> 25:18.345
Like Nephi, commanded
to cut off the head of Laban."

25:18.411 --> 25:19.548
- Mm-hmm?

25:22.955 --> 25:26.028
[Erica babbles]
- Hmm?

25:26.094 --> 25:27.898
[Erica babbles]

25:27.964 --> 25:31.070
BRENDA: Sit like that,
and this go here.

25:33.108 --> 25:36.047
[Erica babbling]

25:46.435 --> 25:48.807
DAN: Hi.
- [gasps]

25:48.873 --> 25:50.075
DAN:
How's it going?

25:50.142 --> 25:52.179
BRENDA:
What are you doing in my house?

25:52.246 --> 25:55.352
DAN: Oh, what am I doing here?
Well, we're family.

25:55.419 --> 25:58.292
Need a reason?
[chuckles]

25:58.358 --> 26:00.597
- I think you need to leave.

26:00.663 --> 26:01.999
DAN:
Oh.

26:02.066 --> 26:05.272
[glass clinking]

26:05.339 --> 26:07.611
Well, I think...

26:07.678 --> 26:09.548
that you...

26:09.614 --> 26:12.620
need to stop driving wedges.

26:12.687 --> 26:14.724
That's what I think.

26:16.762 --> 26:18.933
Allen must return to us.

26:19.000 --> 26:23.274
And you, you will bring Dianna
back to Ron's side.

26:24.845 --> 26:26.348
Immediately.

26:26.414 --> 26:27.650
- Please leave.

26:29.253 --> 26:31.424
- Actions have
consequences, Brenda.

26:31.491 --> 26:33.262
You know that.

26:33.328 --> 26:35.399
- Are you threatening me?

26:35.465 --> 26:37.470
- No.

26:37.537 --> 26:39.542
I am but the hand of God.

26:39.608 --> 26:41.778
It is His mouth
that commands me.

26:43.916 --> 26:47.657
Now, if you obey,
you will be forgiven.

26:47.724 --> 26:49.393
Does that sound fair...

26:52.333 --> 26:53.736
Sister?

26:58.646 --> 26:59.615
Okay.

26:59.682 --> 27:06.795
♪♪ ♪♪

27:10.302 --> 27:11.839
JEB:
"And lo, his hand left her

27:11.905 --> 27:13.208
to contemplate
her transgressions."

27:13.274 --> 27:15.246
It's like he thinks
he's writing a sequel

27:15.312 --> 27:17.216
to the Book of Mormon.

27:17.283 --> 27:19.955
Okay, so the next one,
this one's from Reno.

27:20.022 --> 27:21.358
So when their school
and their family

27:21.424 --> 27:22.794
didn't come running back,
it seems like

27:22.861 --> 27:24.430
they went hunting for converts

27:24.498 --> 27:27.971
to start their own
new School of the Prophets.

27:28.038 --> 27:29.774
They followed through
with some contacts

27:29.841 --> 27:31.278
from the--the last meeting
of the minds,

27:31.344 --> 27:33.014
a few potentials,
some standouts.

27:33.081 --> 27:35.385
In particular,
someone named Sandy.

27:37.791 --> 27:39.828
"And lo, how Sandy provideth

27:39.895 --> 27:42.667
"a roof, warmth,
and nourishment

27:42.734 --> 27:44.304
"from the belly
of the beast's abode,

27:44.370 --> 27:45.707
Circus Circus."

27:45.773 --> 27:47.810
Also, two fellas
who happen to be roommates...

27:49.413 --> 27:53.455
He wrote their whole names,
Ricky Knapp and Chip Carnes.

27:53.523 --> 27:55.092
BILL:
Ricky and Chip?

27:55.159 --> 27:58.700
Those are the two
Doreen told us about.

27:58.767 --> 28:00.268
And they crossed state lines.

28:00.335 --> 28:02.440
We can pull in
the FBI now, Jeb.

28:02.507 --> 28:05.445
- Yeah. Wait, Dan wrote this
ten days ago.

28:05.513 --> 28:07.951
Ron said it was time
to start killing ten days ago.

28:08.018 --> 28:10.890
And then the next morning,
Brenda receives a call

28:10.957 --> 28:12.827
from a Florida payphone.
That's Dianna.

28:12.894 --> 28:15.500
Ten minutes later,
she calls this number,

28:15.566 --> 28:18.539
the office
to the president of the church.

28:18.605 --> 28:20.844
That is as bold as it gets,

28:20.911 --> 28:22.814
for a woman
to call the prophet.

28:22.881 --> 28:25.051
- Women can't call him?
JEB: No one does.

28:25.118 --> 28:27.123
So something must have
really scared them both

28:27.189 --> 28:28.893
to the point
where Dianna was scared enough

28:28.960 --> 28:30.195
to run away
from an apartment

28:30.261 --> 28:32.735
that she knew that Ron
had the address to.

28:32.801 --> 28:34.003
When did, um...

28:36.742 --> 28:37.777
Yeah, the cashier.

28:37.844 --> 28:40.449
The cashier said
that she last saw Dianna

28:40.516 --> 28:42.019
four days ago in her store.

28:42.086 --> 28:46.127
That's--that is the day

28:46.194 --> 28:47.898
that Brenda was killed.

28:47.964 --> 28:49.901
And if that's true,
then Onias was wrong.

28:49.968 --> 28:52.507
They went after Brenda first,
so--

28:52.574 --> 28:56.280
so Dianna might be
out there still alive.

28:56.347 --> 28:58.418
We gotta get to Florida.

28:58.484 --> 29:00.756
Get us plane tickets.

29:00.823 --> 29:01.992
REBECCA: I'm disappointed
you won't be

29:02.059 --> 29:03.629
bearing your testimony.

29:03.696 --> 29:04.932
JEB: Bearing my testimony
can wait

29:04.998 --> 29:07.169
until next month's meeting.

29:07.236 --> 29:08.672
REBECCA: I don't doubt
there will arise

29:08.739 --> 29:10.342
some fresh, new hurdle
next month.

29:12.914 --> 29:14.951
- This isn't
a simple case, Becca.

29:30.048 --> 29:32.486
- Jeb,
he's my General Authority too.

29:44.309 --> 29:46.615
- Just so you know, he told me
that it was the Holy Spirit

29:46.682 --> 29:47.951
that sent him and not you.

29:48.018 --> 29:49.253
They're all liars.

29:51.892 --> 29:54.463
- I went to him
with my concerns,

29:54.531 --> 29:57.069
and now he called to tell me
how you resisted him.

29:57.135 --> 29:59.240
- How could you
go behind my back

29:59.307 --> 30:02.212
and interfere like this?
- Interfere?

30:02.279 --> 30:03.949
- You're not to talk
to him again, you understand?

30:04.016 --> 30:05.085
Unless you have my permission.

30:05.152 --> 30:07.089
- I must obey.
Right, Jebediah?

30:10.930 --> 30:14.470
My dad is coming up
from Arizona

30:14.538 --> 30:17.009
to get me and the girls.

30:17.076 --> 30:19.279
I won't keep subjecting them
to this.

30:38.285 --> 30:40.422
- You know, Becca,
our own founders, they, um...

30:42.459 --> 30:46.100
They saw little girls
and women, all of them,

30:46.167 --> 30:49.207
as eternal servants.

30:49.273 --> 30:51.612
They were taught to be
obedient and submissive.

30:51.678 --> 30:52.847
They were even abused,

30:52.914 --> 30:55.218
some of them raped.

30:55.285 --> 30:57.189
And you should see the things

30:57.255 --> 31:00.896
that Annie is already writing
in her journals.

31:06.875 --> 31:09.581
- I ma--

31:09.647 --> 31:11.619
I married a man of faith,

31:11.685 --> 31:13.756
and that's who I plan
to raise them with,

31:13.822 --> 31:16.762
whether that's you...

31:16.829 --> 31:18.331
or somebody else.

31:21.170 --> 31:22.272
ANNIE:
Mommy?

31:29.186 --> 31:30.990
REBECCA:
Yes, sweetie?

31:31.057 --> 31:33.327
♪♪ ♪♪

31:39.508 --> 31:42.412
[tense music]

31:42.479 --> 31:45.987
♪♪ ♪♪

31:46.054 --> 31:49.159
[indistinct chatter]

31:50.796 --> 31:54.404
BILL: FBI's located Ron's car
outside a home in Cheyenne.

31:54.470 --> 31:55.840
The owner of the house
is the brother

31:55.906 --> 31:58.278
of a Mr. Chip Carnes.

31:58.345 --> 32:01.384
- Okay, well, get your tails
to Wyoming, not Florida.

32:01.451 --> 32:03.087
Go on. Get going.
JEB: Thank you, sir.

32:03.154 --> 32:05.693
CHIEF: Jeb.
JEB: Yeah?

32:05.760 --> 32:08.999
- End this before it does
any more damage to what...

32:09.066 --> 32:12.105
I hope still matters most
to you, Brother.

32:13.976 --> 32:16.113
JEB:
Thank you, sir.

32:16.180 --> 32:22.292
♪♪ ♪♪

32:23.629 --> 32:26.802
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

32:26.869 --> 32:28.505
OFFICER 1: Go. Go.

32:28.572 --> 32:31.512
[indistinct chatter]

32:31.579 --> 32:34.483
[tense music]

32:34.551 --> 32:35.720
♪♪ ♪♪

32:35.787 --> 32:37.022
OFFICER 1:
Go, go, go!

32:37.089 --> 32:39.293
♪♪ ♪♪

32:39.360 --> 32:41.363
OFFICER 1: Move! Move!
OFFICER 2: Right there!

32:41.430 --> 32:42.500
Where I can see them!
OFFICER 3: Freeze!

32:42.567 --> 32:43.536
- Don't shoot.

32:43.602 --> 32:45.338
[panting]
Please.

32:45.405 --> 32:47.410
JEB: No.
RICKY: Please.

32:47.476 --> 32:49.748
OFFICER 2:
Everything's clear.

32:49.815 --> 32:50.917
BILL:
Watch out, huh?

32:50.984 --> 32:51.919
Stand up.
I'll cover him.

32:51.985 --> 32:52.954
JEB:
Watch out.

32:53.021 --> 32:54.725
- Stand up.
Turn around.

32:54.791 --> 32:57.797
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

32:57.864 --> 33:05.011
♪♪ ♪♪

33:18.639 --> 33:20.308
JEB: Anything?
OFFICER 1: All clear.

33:25.385 --> 33:26.453
OFFICER 3:
All clear.

33:27.990 --> 33:30.563
JEB:
Where are Ron and Dan now?

33:30.630 --> 33:32.600
Hey, you can make this as
difficult as you wanna make it,

33:32.667 --> 33:34.971
but in Utah,
you're convicted of murder,

33:35.038 --> 33:36.040
that's a death sentence.

33:36.107 --> 33:37.510
BILL:
You know what that means?

33:37.577 --> 33:40.348
Four high-powered rounds
that'll rip your chest open.

33:40.415 --> 33:42.219
It's what Utah does
to child killers.

33:42.286 --> 33:44.356
- No, we left Ron and Dan
in Nevada.

33:44.423 --> 33:46.160
BILL: And when was this?
- Four days ago.

33:46.227 --> 33:47.462
JEB:
Where in Nevada?

33:47.530 --> 33:50.101
- Uh, at a motel room
just over the state line.

33:50.168 --> 33:52.239
- We got pulled over
for a busted taillight,

33:52.306 --> 33:54.409
and trooper let us go.
- Ron got nervous.

33:54.476 --> 33:56.280
Got us a motel room
for the night.

33:56.347 --> 33:59.654
I-I only started hangin' out
with Dan 'cause he was

33:59.721 --> 34:01.591
a good time at first.
- So what changed?

34:01.658 --> 34:04.096
CHIP:
All of the heaven talk, man.

34:04.163 --> 34:06.000
It just got so fucking crazy.

34:06.067 --> 34:08.138
- I don't even believe in God.

34:08.204 --> 34:09.507
Fuck God.

34:10.710 --> 34:12.179
BILL: Where were they headed?
- Reno.

34:12.246 --> 34:13.181
RICKY: Reno.

34:13.248 --> 34:14.551
That's where Ron

34:14.618 --> 34:16.220
wanted to go
make some quick cash.

34:16.287 --> 34:18.592
- What'd they need cash for?
- To, uh...

34:18.659 --> 34:21.498
♪♪ ♪♪

34:21.565 --> 34:23.702
- To finish their list.
- Finish their list.

34:23.769 --> 34:25.339
♪♪ ♪♪

34:25.405 --> 34:26.575
- Why do you have Ron's car?

34:26.642 --> 34:30.182
- We stole it, Chip and I,
to get away from them.

34:30.248 --> 34:33.088
The--the blood.

34:33.154 --> 34:34.223
You don't understand.

34:34.290 --> 34:36.260
There was so much blood,
you could--

34:36.327 --> 34:38.866
you could smell the iron in it.

34:38.933 --> 34:43.575
♪♪ ♪♪

34:43.642 --> 34:45.646
JEB: So what happened
on the day of the murder?

34:47.349 --> 34:49.219
[indistinct chatter]

34:49.286 --> 34:51.157
[saw buzzing]

34:51.223 --> 34:53.695
- Are we six now, Ron?

34:53.762 --> 34:54.998
If so, I ain't getting
in the back.

34:55.065 --> 34:55.967
DAN: Hey.
[clears throat]

34:56.033 --> 34:57.637
Sam. Sam.
RON: Dan. Dan.

34:57.703 --> 35:00.108
DAN: So Ron had
a revelation last night,

35:00.175 --> 35:02.814
and He says
the Heavenly Father

35:02.881 --> 35:05.753
says you and Jacob
were not called on this.

35:05.819 --> 35:07.122
SAM:
No.

35:07.189 --> 35:09.360
Ron, Ron,
we can leave Jacob with Mom.

35:09.426 --> 35:10.663
I'm your flesh and blood, Dan!
DAN: Right.

35:10.730 --> 35:13.434
Which is why
the Lord has called on you

35:13.502 --> 35:16.641
to stay here and to care
for Mom and Jacob.

35:16.708 --> 35:18.879
Heavenly Father wants you
to do all that you can

35:18.945 --> 35:20.549
to protect our family

35:20.616 --> 35:22.520
while we go off
and do His work.

35:22.587 --> 35:24.524
RICKY: We left after breakfast,
the four of us.

35:24.591 --> 35:27.797
We went to, uh, Robin's house.

35:27.864 --> 35:30.770
[soft dramatic music]

35:30.837 --> 35:33.274
♪♪ ♪♪

35:33.341 --> 35:35.478
[knocking]

35:40.354 --> 35:42.092
- Go get your hunting rifle.

35:42.159 --> 35:43.395
.243.
Go get it.

35:43.461 --> 35:44.898
- Uh, I don't have it here.

35:44.965 --> 35:47.135
It's, um--I lent it to Allen.

35:47.202 --> 35:48.672
Why?
- Really?

35:52.646 --> 35:53.715
ROBIN:
What are you--

35:56.721 --> 36:00.028
Look, Ron, I'm sorry I-I made
a mistake about the horses.

36:00.095 --> 36:02.232
I-I should have listened
to you.

36:03.468 --> 36:05.740
And I don't know what this is.

36:05.806 --> 36:06.875
Whatever you're doing,
you don't have to--

36:06.942 --> 36:07.977
Ron.
Ron, please.

36:08.044 --> 36:14.891
♪♪ ♪♪

36:16.895 --> 36:20.068
Ron, what--what--

36:20.134 --> 36:21.470
what are you hunting for?

36:22.940 --> 36:24.978
- Oh, anything
that gets in our way.

36:25.045 --> 36:31.991
♪♪ ♪♪

36:35.098 --> 36:37.235
[knocking]

36:37.302 --> 36:44.416
♪♪ ♪♪

36:47.723 --> 36:49.426
[knocking]

36:53.802 --> 36:56.174
[knocking]

36:56.240 --> 36:59.379
[phone ringing]

37:00.950 --> 37:06.260
♪♪ ♪♪

37:06.327 --> 37:08.431
[ringing continues]

37:08.499 --> 37:15.144
♪♪ ♪♪

37:15.211 --> 37:16.213
- Hello.

37:16.280 --> 37:17.651
ALLEN:
Hey.

37:17.717 --> 37:19.921
- [sighs]
ALLEN: Everything okay?

37:19.988 --> 37:22.425
- Um, I, um--

37:22.493 --> 37:25.031
I-I think there was
someone at the door.

37:25.098 --> 37:27.737
ALLEN: Okay.
Do you need to go get it?

37:27.804 --> 37:30.007
- I don't know, it's just,
since Dan broke in...

37:30.074 --> 37:31.878
ALLEN:
Hey, hey.

37:31.945 --> 37:34.382
Look, I can protect you
from them.

37:36.254 --> 37:37.757
- Okay.

37:37.824 --> 37:40.495
ALLEN: I-I just really
wanted to hear your voice.

37:40.562 --> 37:42.465
- Really?
ALLEN: Really.

37:44.302 --> 37:45.940
Hey, sorry.

37:46.006 --> 37:47.710
I-I gotta go.
I gotta finish here.

37:47.777 --> 37:49.246
I'll get home
as soon as I can.

37:49.313 --> 37:51.985
And maybe we could go watch
the Pioneer Day fireworks.

37:52.052 --> 37:54.189
- Yes, please.
[laughs]

37:54.256 --> 37:56.393
Okay, I'll see you real soon.

37:56.460 --> 37:57.763
ALLEN:
See you.

38:27.389 --> 38:30.495
[indistinct chatter]

38:47.363 --> 38:48.565
- [squeals]

38:55.078 --> 38:57.984
[suspenseful music]

38:58.051 --> 39:03.027
♪♪ ♪♪

39:03.094 --> 39:04.897
- Why'd you stop there?

39:04.964 --> 39:08.270
- That's where Ron
started to lose it, yeah.

39:08.337 --> 39:12.680
♪♪ ♪♪

39:12.747 --> 39:14.550
- Maybe this was
a test of our faith.

39:14.617 --> 39:18.391
♪♪ ♪♪

39:18.457 --> 39:19.794
- Have you lost
your will, Brother?

39:19.861 --> 39:21.296
♪♪ ♪♪

39:21.363 --> 39:24.302
[Erica crying]

39:24.369 --> 39:28.210
♪♪ ♪♪

39:28.277 --> 39:30.649
Ron, what if...
- One.

39:30.716 --> 39:31.951
- Maybe--
- Not two.

39:32.018 --> 39:33.454
[Erica crying]

39:33.522 --> 39:36.260
- Ron, what if--

39:36.326 --> 39:37.797
what if...
RON: Fuck!

39:37.863 --> 39:40.602
- You were only meant
to lead us this far?

39:40.669 --> 39:43.107
♪♪ ♪♪

39:43.174 --> 39:47.315
I have long prayed
for a sacrifice so great

39:47.382 --> 39:49.821
that I might be able to prove
that I will do anything

39:49.887 --> 39:51.725
and go anywhere
for Heavenly Father.

39:51.791 --> 39:54.230
And I can hear Him.
I can hear Him.

39:54.296 --> 39:55.999
RON: One.
- And it is His command

39:56.066 --> 39:58.337
that I set His church
back in order now.

39:58.404 --> 40:00.842
- Six.
[wheezing]

40:02.580 --> 40:04.082
DAN:
Do you hear Him say that?

40:07.255 --> 40:09.627
He's saying...

40:09.694 --> 40:12.934
that it is now I...

40:13.000 --> 40:15.606
who is going to set
His church back in order.

40:15.672 --> 40:18.612
[dramatic music]

40:18.679 --> 40:24.423
♪♪ ♪♪

40:24.490 --> 40:26.026
[car horn honks]

40:26.093 --> 40:33.007
♪♪ ♪♪

40:37.015 --> 40:41.090
- ♪♪ And if that mockingbird
don't sing ♪♪

40:41.157 --> 40:48.103
♪♪ ♪♪

40:50.742 --> 40:54.751
July 24th, 1984.

40:54.817 --> 40:57.189
Dear Dianna,
these past few months

40:57.255 --> 40:59.660
have been the hardest
of my life.

40:59.727 --> 41:05.605
♪♪ ♪♪

41:07.710 --> 41:08.845
[door clicks shut]

41:16.260 --> 41:19.199
[ominous music]

41:19.266 --> 41:26.213
♪♪ ♪♪

41:52.131 --> 41:53.802
[knocking]

42:02.586 --> 42:04.591
BRENDA:
[gasps] No! No!

42:04.657 --> 42:07.796
[door thumping]

42:07.863 --> 42:10.168
Please!
DAN: Get over here!

42:10.235 --> 42:17.148
♪♪ ♪♪

42:24.931 --> 42:26.934
- Oh, my God.
CHIP: Oh, man.

42:28.437 --> 42:29.807
Oh...

42:38.625 --> 42:45.606
♪♪ ♪♪

42:45.673 --> 42:47.208
BRENDA: Please!
[both grunt]

42:47.275 --> 42:49.948
[Brenda wheezing]

42:50.015 --> 42:51.718
RON:
Daniel, what do we do?

42:51.784 --> 42:53.253
BRENDA:
Ron. Ron.

42:53.320 --> 42:55.424
- We must start completing
your revelations now, Brother.

42:55.491 --> 42:56.661
BRENDA:
Stop him, please.

42:56.728 --> 42:58.097
DAN: If you've truly heard
the voice of God,

42:58.164 --> 42:59.733
then you will
hand me the blades.

43:01.437 --> 43:04.109
The blades, do you have them?
BRENDA: Please stop him.

43:04.176 --> 43:08.217
♪♪ ♪♪

43:08.284 --> 43:10.689
No!
DAN: You should knock her out.

43:10.756 --> 43:12.526
BRENDA:
No! No!

43:12.593 --> 43:14.664
No! No!

43:14.731 --> 43:16.535
Please. Please, Ron.
Please, Ron.

43:16.601 --> 43:18.237
Stop him!

43:18.304 --> 43:19.439
Please, Ron.

43:19.507 --> 43:21.443
Ron, don't do this.
Ron.

43:21.511 --> 43:28.123
♪♪ ♪♪

43:28.190 --> 43:31.063
[Erica crying]

43:31.130 --> 43:38.076
♪♪ ♪♪

43:39.714 --> 43:41.183
Please.

43:43.287 --> 43:45.626
Dan, what do you want?

43:45.693 --> 43:47.964
Ron.
Ron, look at me.

43:48.030 --> 43:50.067
Heavenly Father knows.

43:50.134 --> 43:52.405
He knows
this isn't who you are.

43:54.342 --> 43:55.478
It isn't.

43:55.545 --> 43:57.215
It isn't His voice you hear.

43:57.282 --> 43:58.785
[Erica crying]

43:58.852 --> 44:01.256
Please think
of your own children.

44:01.323 --> 44:02.358
DAN:
God's will.

44:02.425 --> 44:04.362
Take care. There's nothing
you could've done.

44:04.429 --> 44:07.401
[Erica crying]

44:07.468 --> 44:10.041
[soft dramatic music]

44:10.107 --> 44:13.581
- The selfish,
the cowardly...

44:13.648 --> 44:15.752
♪♪ ♪♪

44:15.819 --> 44:17.756
The murderers and liars...

44:17.823 --> 44:19.861
♪♪ ♪♪

44:19.927 --> 44:21.631
Their portion
will be in the lake...

44:21.698 --> 44:24.169
♪♪ ♪♪

44:24.236 --> 44:26.607
That burns
with fire and sulfur...

44:26.674 --> 44:28.845
♪♪ ♪♪

44:28.912 --> 44:29.847
[Erica crying]

44:29.914 --> 44:32.185
Which will be
your second deaths.

44:32.252 --> 44:36.092
♪♪ ♪♪

44:36.159 --> 44:38.364
God will make me whole again...

44:38.431 --> 44:42.271
♪♪ ♪♪

44:42.338 --> 44:47.348
And send you both
into everlasting darkness.

44:47.415 --> 44:49.419
♪♪ ♪♪

44:49.486 --> 44:50.890
No! No! No!

44:50.956 --> 44:54.697
[crying echoes]

45:02.780 --> 45:04.349
RICKY:
Dan did it.

45:04.415 --> 45:05.820
He cut Brenda's neck.

45:05.886 --> 45:08.825
[dark music]

45:08.892 --> 45:10.895
♪♪ ♪♪

45:10.962 --> 45:12.833
Ron gave him a cord
to tie around it

45:12.900 --> 45:14.637
to make sure that it was done,

45:14.704 --> 45:17.576
but then,

45:17.643 --> 45:19.680
Dan cut her baby's neck too.

45:19.747 --> 45:26.861
♪♪ ♪♪

45:37.248 --> 45:39.186
Dan drove to another home
after that,

45:39.253 --> 45:41.691
but thank God no one was home.

45:41.758 --> 45:44.897
♪♪ ♪♪

45:44.964 --> 45:46.968
He missed the turn
to their third target,

45:47.034 --> 45:51.944
and, uh, Dan said
it was a sign from God

45:52.011 --> 45:54.248
that they needed
to stop killing

45:54.315 --> 45:57.957
till they made enough cash
to keep going.

45:58.024 --> 46:00.929
But if you ask me,

46:00.996 --> 46:03.535
Dan knew he needed
to get Ron focused again.

46:03.602 --> 46:05.773
- Focused on?

46:05.840 --> 46:07.174
- On Dianna.

46:08.812 --> 46:12.820
Dan brought her up every minute
on our way to Nevada.

46:12.887 --> 46:16.226
Ron didn't say much,
but when he did,

46:16.293 --> 46:20.602
it was always about
atoning his wife and kids.

46:20.669 --> 46:27.816
♪♪ ♪♪

46:30.421 --> 46:32.993
BILL: At the state sign,
slow down.

46:33.060 --> 46:35.231
Now stop.
We got tracks over here.

46:35.298 --> 46:42.244
♪♪ ♪♪

46:43.480 --> 46:45.317
That looks like luggage.

46:45.384 --> 46:52.298
♪♪ ♪♪

47:08.899 --> 47:09.967
- It's the blades
he wanted blessed

47:10.034 --> 47:11.436
for blood atonement

47:11.504 --> 47:13.942
all alone in a case
with his name on it.

47:14.008 --> 47:16.112
- Well, in the end,
they want the credit.

47:16.179 --> 47:17.549
- Or it's a threat.

47:19.587 --> 47:23.293
It's a threat to any cop who
dares to pursue God's warriors.

47:25.431 --> 47:27.402
Problem is,
is the--the coroner said

47:27.468 --> 47:29.072
that they used
something long and crude,

47:29.139 --> 47:30.542
and so, these aren't
the murder weapons.

47:32.211 --> 47:35.084
Ricky and Chip said the
murder weapon would be here.

47:35.151 --> 47:36.486
Bill, if they were
lying about this,

47:36.554 --> 47:39.894
what if Reno
is just a story too?

47:39.960 --> 47:42.265
Maybe Dan and Ron
are already in Florida

47:42.331 --> 47:43.734
hunting Dianna and her kids.

47:43.801 --> 47:46.541
A wrong turn here, Bill,
and a lot more people die.

47:46.607 --> 47:47.441
Kids die.

47:47.509 --> 47:48.879
- Did Ricky claim
to be an atheist?

47:48.945 --> 47:51.349
JEB: Yeah.
- Well, so did Chip.

47:51.416 --> 47:53.789
So they got nothing
to gain from any God

47:53.855 --> 47:55.457
by protecting Ron or Dan,

47:55.525 --> 47:57.462
and they both said Reno.

47:57.530 --> 47:59.867
- When I was a boy,
I-I was taught that atheists

47:59.934 --> 48:02.471
were put on Earth
to lead us astray,

48:02.539 --> 48:05.144
and now you want me to entrust
all these innocent lives

48:05.211 --> 48:06.747
with a pair of 'em?

48:06.814 --> 48:09.052
- Jeb, I'm very well aware

48:09.118 --> 48:11.489
that your sporadically
compassionate people

48:11.557 --> 48:12.826
have an allergy to facts

48:12.893 --> 48:15.765
because facts
point toward truth.

48:15.832 --> 48:17.502
Take your church leader's story

48:17.569 --> 48:20.776
about our people
saving Zion together.

48:20.843 --> 48:24.282
My great-grandpa told it
a different way.

48:24.349 --> 48:26.821
The Fanchers were a wealthy
wagon train from Arkansas,

48:26.888 --> 48:29.326
not from anywhere near
where Joseph was murdered.

48:29.392 --> 48:31.598
They were no threat
to your people.

48:31.664 --> 48:33.033
There was no cannons,

48:33.100 --> 48:35.071
no bluecoats.

48:35.137 --> 48:36.339
They weren't an army at all.

48:37.910 --> 48:40.281
- Heavenly Father will protect

48:40.347 --> 48:43.053
His brave and loyal servants

48:43.119 --> 48:44.757
from the Gentiles' bullets!

48:44.824 --> 48:46.292
Attack!

48:47.863 --> 48:49.432
[gunshot]

48:49.500 --> 48:51.704
BILL: Your Mormon leaders
wanted to send a message

48:51.771 --> 48:53.107
to America

48:53.174 --> 48:55.277
that any Gentile entering Utah

48:55.344 --> 48:56.948
risked their lives,

48:57.015 --> 49:00.154
and they planned to place
the blame at my people's feet.

49:00.221 --> 49:02.291
- What is this game?

49:02.358 --> 49:04.262
Why are your men
dressed up as Paiute?

49:04.329 --> 49:05.999
MAJOR LEE:
There's no time for questions.

49:06.065 --> 49:08.505
You fight, or you starve.
That's your choice.

49:08.571 --> 49:11.009
BILL: My people knew
that to refuse Brigham

49:11.076 --> 49:13.815
was to make an enemy
of their occupier,

49:13.882 --> 49:15.618
a man unafraid to shed blood.

49:17.054 --> 49:18.725
But they had been lied to.

49:18.792 --> 49:20.895
- Your prophet lies.

49:20.962 --> 49:22.365
You lie.

49:22.432 --> 49:25.706
You want the shame of this day
on our people.

49:25.772 --> 49:28.043
[gunshot]

49:28.109 --> 49:29.580
[shouting in Paiute]
MAJOR LEE: No, no, no.

49:29.646 --> 49:32.385
You can't abandon me!
Get back here!

49:32.452 --> 49:34.322
If you abandon God's army now,

49:34.388 --> 49:36.426
your blood
will stain His Earth next!

49:38.998 --> 49:40.267
Paint your faces.

49:40.334 --> 49:42.807
Use grease.
Use mud.

49:42.873 --> 49:44.175
You're all Indian now!

49:44.242 --> 49:46.279
- Different facts.

49:46.346 --> 49:48.919
MAJOR LEE: I mean no harm
to my Christian brothers!

49:48.985 --> 49:51.089
[dramatic music]

49:51.156 --> 49:52.926
I bring you fresh water!

49:52.993 --> 49:56.132
♪♪ ♪♪

49:56.199 --> 49:57.936
- Any mention
of that version of history

49:58.003 --> 50:00.609
has vanished
from BYU's libraries.

50:00.676 --> 50:04.416
- State your name.
- I'm Major John D. Lee.

50:04.482 --> 50:06.353
I'm the Indian agent
in these parts.

50:06.420 --> 50:08.157
- We're only passing through.

50:08.224 --> 50:09.727
We have no plans
to take their land.

50:09.793 --> 50:14.035
- These hills here are ringed
with Indian fighters.

50:14.101 --> 50:15.470
You're outnumbered, friend.

50:16.840 --> 50:18.711
But I have ear of the chief,

50:18.778 --> 50:21.383
and I've negotiated
a compromise.

50:21.449 --> 50:22.886
If you hand over your arms,

50:22.953 --> 50:25.257
I'll pilot you
past the Paiute,

50:25.324 --> 50:28.164
who right now

50:28.230 --> 50:31.169
are organizing
a final push against you.

50:32.371 --> 50:34.777
- I will consider it, Major.

50:34.844 --> 50:37.983
- I would consider
your children, sir.

50:38.050 --> 50:42.759
♪♪ ♪♪

50:42.826 --> 50:45.598
BILL: Only Gentiles
and "Injuns" were killed,

50:45.665 --> 50:49.205
so why risk the church's
reputation for my dark skin?

50:49.272 --> 50:52.478
If you aren't white,
LDS, and a man in Zion,

50:52.546 --> 50:55.184
your life is of little value.

50:55.250 --> 50:57.121
Is that the way you see me?

50:58.658 --> 50:59.994
Mormon myths?

51:00.060 --> 51:01.797
Lies?

51:01.864 --> 51:04.603
Is that what you want
to keep puttin' your trust in?

51:04.670 --> 51:07.742
Or do you think we can
start trusting the facts?

51:10.481 --> 51:12.986
Even if they do come
from a pair of atheists?

51:13.053 --> 51:15.324
♪♪ ♪♪

51:15.391 --> 51:17.729
Right where Chip said
they threw it from the car.

51:17.796 --> 51:23.641
♪♪ ♪♪

51:23.708 --> 51:24.910
They weren't lying.

51:24.977 --> 51:26.747
♪♪ ♪♪

51:26.814 --> 51:30.889
That's a skill particular
to your ancestors, Jeb.

51:30.956 --> 51:37.836
♪♪ ♪♪

51:39.105 --> 51:41.042
[whistle blows]

51:41.109 --> 51:42.946
- Saints, do your duty!

51:43.013 --> 51:45.885
[gunshots]

51:45.952 --> 51:47.956
♪♪ ♪♪

51:48.023 --> 51:51.229
[people screaming]

51:51.296 --> 51:58.443
♪♪ ♪♪

52:10.769 --> 52:11.904
[cow moos]

52:29.305 --> 52:32.244
[pensive music]

52:32.311 --> 52:39.458
♪♪ ♪♪

52:41.964 --> 52:44.703
JEB:
"And lo, how Sandy provideth

52:44.770 --> 52:47.543
"a roof, warmth,
and nourishment

52:47.609 --> 52:50.114
"from the belly
of the beast's abode,

52:50.180 --> 52:51.650
Circus Circus."

52:51.717 --> 52:55.124
STEELY DAN: ♪♪ In the mornin',
you go gunnin' ♪♪

52:55.190 --> 52:56.494
♪♪ For the man ♪♪

52:56.561 --> 52:58.464
JEB: The last time
we saw Dan and Ron,

52:58.531 --> 53:01.336
they had beards
like Brigham Young.

53:01.403 --> 53:02.672
BILL:
Think Old Testament,

53:02.739 --> 53:04.342
Charlton Heston
in Ten Commandments.

53:04.409 --> 53:05.612
RENO COP:
It's a problem.

53:05.678 --> 53:07.281
They commit the crime
looking like Moses,

53:07.348 --> 53:09.787
shave it off,
and your clue's dead cold.

53:09.853 --> 53:11.691
- I don't think
they wanna hide from this.

53:11.758 --> 53:14.428
This--this may sound
a little nutty to you both,

53:14.496 --> 53:18.337
but I think
they're proud of this.

53:18.403 --> 53:20.274
- Right.
We'll check with security.

53:20.341 --> 53:21.744
JEB: Okay, that's all
I'm asking. Thank you.

53:21.810 --> 53:24.750
[dramatic music]

53:24.817 --> 53:26.219
♪♪ ♪♪

53:26.286 --> 53:29.125
GARY: Right there.
Is that your Sandy?

53:29.192 --> 53:35.237
♪♪ ♪♪

53:35.303 --> 53:37.676
JEB: Could be.
Let's keep an eye on her.

53:37.743 --> 53:39.178
Don't wanna
take her in too soon.

53:39.245 --> 53:41.416
It might scare Dan and Ron off.

53:41.483 --> 53:43.921
[exhales heavily]

53:43.988 --> 53:45.190
Where is she going now?

53:45.257 --> 53:46.226
GARY:
Backstage.

53:46.293 --> 53:48.163
Toilet break.

53:48.229 --> 53:49.967
- That's where everyone goes?
GARY: No.

53:50.033 --> 53:51.804
I take all my shits at home.

53:51.871 --> 53:53.975
- Can you share with me
any more of her details?

53:54.042 --> 53:56.245
Uh, full name, address?

53:56.312 --> 53:57.314
- Not to tell you
how to do your job,

53:57.381 --> 53:58.718
but you need a judge for that.

53:58.785 --> 54:00.622
- You know this case
has crossed state lines now?

54:00.689 --> 54:02.358
So if we don't solve it soon,

54:02.424 --> 54:04.530
this whole place
is gonna be crawling with FBI.

54:04.597 --> 54:06.600
And I know there's one thing
our people have in common,

54:06.667 --> 54:08.738
is that we hate
having the feds in our home.

54:08.804 --> 54:10.407
So a little help, Gary?
BILLY: Jeb. Jeb.

54:14.115 --> 54:15.418
I'll get a warrant,

54:15.484 --> 54:16.920
I'll search her house,

54:16.987 --> 54:19.893
and if it's clear,
I'll keep watch out outside.

54:19.960 --> 54:21.497
All night.

54:21.564 --> 54:23.935
I need you
to get some sleep.

54:24.001 --> 54:26.907
[soft rock music]

54:26.974 --> 54:31.917
♪♪ ♪♪

54:36.527 --> 54:39.599
[radio chatter]

54:40.969 --> 54:42.973
[car approaching]

54:43.040 --> 54:44.543
[radio clicks off]

54:50.387 --> 54:52.224
[engine shuts off]

54:52.291 --> 54:53.226
[car door slams]

54:53.293 --> 54:56.232
[sirens wailing]

54:56.299 --> 54:59.205
[tense music]

54:59.272 --> 55:06.419
♪♪ ♪♪

55:19.312 --> 55:20.948
[low radio chatter]

55:21.015 --> 55:23.554
[door creaks]

55:23.621 --> 55:27.127
DAN: And the Lord will send
One Mighty and Strong,

55:27.194 --> 55:28.498
holding the scepter of power--

55:28.564 --> 55:29.967
[both grunting]

55:30.034 --> 55:31.670
[Jeb gasping]

55:31.737 --> 55:33.841
DAN:
For this, I...

55:33.908 --> 55:34.943
I am His One.

55:35.010 --> 55:41.957
♪♪ ♪♪

55:53.614 --> 55:56.720
[phone ringing]

56:00.094 --> 56:01.362
JEB: Hello.

56:01.429 --> 56:03.835
LOPEZ: Detective Pyre.
- Yeah, it's me.

56:03.901 --> 56:05.538
LOPEZ: [exhales heavily]
I've been trying to reach you.

56:05.605 --> 56:07.575
Listen, we found
Dianna and her kids.

56:10.047 --> 56:11.282
- Alive or dead?

56:11.349 --> 56:14.757
♪♪ ♪♪

56:14.824 --> 56:16.593
DIANNA: Everybody up.
Come on.

56:16.660 --> 56:20.601
Come with me like I told you.

56:20.668 --> 56:23.574
You lock this door,
and don't open it for anyone,

56:23.641 --> 56:24.576
no matter what you hear.

56:24.643 --> 56:27.348
♪♪ ♪♪

56:27.415 --> 56:31.155
LOPEZ: Listen, it's not
all good news, Detective.

56:31.222 --> 56:32.324
[door bangs open]

56:32.391 --> 56:34.930
♪♪ ♪♪

56:34.997 --> 56:36.901
For very good reason,
she understood

56:36.968 --> 56:38.871
that she and her kids
were being hunted.

56:38.938 --> 56:43.514
♪♪ ♪♪

56:43.581 --> 56:45.719
I'm Detective Lopez.
Where are the children?

56:45.785 --> 56:46.787
DIANNA: In the basement.
They're locked in the basement.

56:46.853 --> 56:47.722
LOPEZ:
Okay.

56:47.789 --> 56:49.760
We got to her first,

56:49.827 --> 56:51.630
but she didn't know Brenda
had already been killed.

56:51.697 --> 56:54.603
[somber music]

56:54.670 --> 56:57.240
♪♪ ♪♪

56:57.307 --> 56:59.445
OFFICER:
Everyone, out.

56:59.513 --> 57:06.626
♪♪ ♪♪

57:10.300 --> 57:12.972
BRENDA:
Dear Dianna,

57:13.039 --> 57:16.747
these past few months have
been the hardest of my life,

57:16.814 --> 57:19.485
but knowing you're safe
brings me such meaning.

57:19.553 --> 57:20.922
♪♪ ♪♪

57:20.989 --> 57:22.925
I just pray I'll reach the day

57:22.992 --> 57:25.665
when I'll be away
from this too,

57:25.731 --> 57:28.738
that our homes
can be united again.

57:28.805 --> 57:31.342
I'd give my life for that,

57:31.409 --> 57:33.881
for I believe
that in order to stand proud

57:33.948 --> 57:36.385
before our Savior
on the last day,

57:36.452 --> 57:39.959
we mothers must
defend our families from evil,

57:40.026 --> 57:42.732
to help men
see past themselves,

57:42.799 --> 57:45.672
and to stand up to those,
even in our church,

57:45.738 --> 57:48.042
who lead us astray

57:48.109 --> 57:50.615
so we may stand glorified
on the last day,

57:50.682 --> 57:55.391
together with you,
my eternal sister,

57:55.457 --> 57:56.492
at my side.

57:56.560 --> 57:58.029
♪♪ ♪♪

57:58.096 --> 57:58.964
Love, Brenda.

57:59.031 --> 58:05.978
♪♪ ♪♪

58:07.949 --> 58:10.921
- Are the other wives safe?

58:10.988 --> 58:12.158
LOPEZ:
The detective in Utah asked

58:12.224 --> 58:14.361
if a Matilda
had been here with you.

58:14.428 --> 58:15.865
DIANNA:
No.

58:15.931 --> 58:17.502
LOPEZ:
Then no, not yet.

58:17.569 --> 58:21.977
♪♪ ♪♪

58:22.044 --> 58:23.914
The kids are
in a safe house now,

58:23.981 --> 58:25.685
but once they settled in,

58:25.752 --> 58:27.354
Dianna disappeared.

58:27.421 --> 58:29.325
Her purse is gone
and her keys are gone,

58:29.392 --> 58:31.496
so she left of her own accord.

58:31.563 --> 58:32.999
I just don't know where to,

58:33.066 --> 58:35.270
and her kids' lips are sealed.

58:35.337 --> 58:37.976
♪♪ ♪♪

58:38.043 --> 58:40.681
BILL: I searched
Sandy's home discreetly.

58:40.748 --> 58:42.384
Ron and Dan aren't there now,
but it looks like

58:42.451 --> 58:44.790
they may have been taken turns
with Sister Sandy.

58:44.856 --> 58:46.459
Lots of old condom wrappers.

58:46.527 --> 58:48.163
JEB:
Premarital sex is forbidden

58:48.229 --> 58:50.467
by LDS laws of chastity,
so maybe she's a, um--

58:50.535 --> 58:52.672
- If your boys didn't mind
committing a double murder,

58:52.739 --> 58:54.308
why worry about forbidden sex?

58:54.375 --> 58:56.914
- Well, they believed
they were allowed to kill

58:56.981 --> 58:59.152
by God's laws, not--
- Well, maybe they married her

58:59.218 --> 59:00.988
by sexual consummation

59:01.055 --> 59:03.928
like Brigham Young
and all his wives, right?

59:03.994 --> 59:06.466
Well, either way,
looks like Dan and Ron

59:06.534 --> 59:08.804
spent some more time with her.

59:08.871 --> 59:10.073
That, or she's a hell of a fan.

59:10.140 --> 59:11.710
PEPPERMILL DEALER:
Oh. Stop there.

59:11.777 --> 59:14.348
Yeah. Yeah, rewind.

59:14.415 --> 59:15.551
All right.
There you go.

59:15.618 --> 59:17.689
There they are, hmm?

59:17.756 --> 59:19.626
Your cops came
to the Peppermill

59:19.692 --> 59:21.630
asking about bearded men.

59:21.697 --> 59:24.134
I remember them right off.

59:24.201 --> 59:25.672
They won big, all right.

59:25.739 --> 59:28.644
Thing is,
most pray before I deal,

59:28.710 --> 59:31.349
then they forget all about God
if they win.

59:31.416 --> 59:35.758
When they won, they got
right down on their knees.

59:38.330 --> 59:41.235
[tense music]

59:41.302 --> 59:47.716
♪♪ ♪♪

59:47.783 --> 59:48.750
[both grunt]

59:48.817 --> 59:50.755
DAN:
I am His One.

59:50.822 --> 59:53.761
♪♪ ♪♪

59:53.827 --> 59:55.463
JEB: The thing
that Dan did with his hand?

59:55.531 --> 59:59.438
♪♪ ♪♪

59:59.506 --> 1:00:02.578
It's part of a sacred
temple oath that we take.

1:00:02.645 --> 1:00:04.582
Rather than
reveal our covenants,

1:00:04.649 --> 1:00:07.187
we'd have our throats cut
ear to ear.

1:00:09.091 --> 1:00:10.662
That wasn't meant
for casino security.

1:00:10.728 --> 1:00:12.765
That was meant for me.

1:00:12.832 --> 1:00:19.612
♪♪ ♪♪

1:00:19.679 --> 1:00:21.917
BILL:
That video is two days old.

1:00:21.983 --> 1:00:23.219
They've had
all the money they need

1:00:23.286 --> 1:00:27.394
to start killing again
for over 48 hours now.

1:00:27.460 --> 1:00:30.100
Why are we still in Reno?

1:00:30.167 --> 1:00:31.236
I need you to use

1:00:31.302 --> 1:00:34.676
every bit of your LDS knowledge
you've got

1:00:34.743 --> 1:00:37.882
and tell me where they are now.

1:00:37.949 --> 1:00:40.755
Is it Utah? Florida?

1:00:40.821 --> 1:00:44.261
According to your God,
who dies next?

1:00:44.328 --> 1:00:48.937
♪♪ ♪♪

1:00:49.004 --> 1:00:50.709
[Dianna inhales, groaning]

1:00:50.775 --> 1:00:53.714
[dramatic music]

1:00:53.781 --> 1:01:00.762
♪♪ ♪♪

1:01:00.828 --> 1:01:03.834
[engine turning over]

1:01:09.178 --> 1:01:11.415
[birds chirping]

1:01:11.482 --> 1:01:14.388
♪♪ ♪♪

1:01:17.762 --> 1:01:19.733
BILL: So you think
she headed back to Utah?

1:01:19.799 --> 1:01:22.505
- I don't know.

1:01:22.572 --> 1:01:26.346
A devout LDS wife would...

1:01:26.412 --> 1:01:29.252
head back
and help her eternal husband.

1:01:29.318 --> 1:01:31.757
They got married in a temple.
That means something.

1:01:31.824 --> 1:01:33.360
[sighs]

1:01:33.426 --> 1:01:35.430
- And Dan and Ron know this?
- Yeah.

1:01:35.498 --> 1:01:36.934
- So they'll just camp out
and wait for her?

1:01:37.000 --> 1:01:40.107
- I don't know, Bill.
I don't know.

1:01:40.173 --> 1:01:42.945
[sighs]
Oh, my gosh.

1:01:43.012 --> 1:01:46.385
How do you do this?
How do you do it?

1:01:46.452 --> 1:01:50.528
Just walking through life
with no compass?

1:01:50.595 --> 1:01:52.063
- You think I have no compass?

1:01:53.934 --> 1:01:55.337
Jeb, are you the kind of man

1:01:55.403 --> 1:01:56.773
who would pinch
his own baby girl

1:01:56.840 --> 1:01:59.144
so you could comfort them
when they cry out?

1:01:59.211 --> 1:02:01.082
- What?
That's insane.

1:02:01.148 --> 1:02:03.987
- So is trying to play hero
to Dianna now.

1:02:04.054 --> 1:02:06.760
Our job is to get the monsters
off her back,

1:02:06.826 --> 1:02:08.062
the ones you've helped feed

1:02:08.129 --> 1:02:10.935
with all your
good Mormon testimony bearing.

1:02:11.002 --> 1:02:14.542
Your responsibility is
to find the men who did this

1:02:14.609 --> 1:02:16.379
and get them off her back.

1:02:16.446 --> 1:02:20.120
Do that, and she'll do
just fine without you.

1:02:20.186 --> 1:02:24.596
So one more time,
where are Dan and Ron?

1:02:24.662 --> 1:02:27.635
[dramatic music]

1:02:27.702 --> 1:02:31.409
♪♪ ♪♪

1:02:31.475 --> 1:02:32.410
- I don't know.

1:02:35.150 --> 1:02:38.222
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

1:02:38.289 --> 1:02:40.528
Hey!

1:02:40.594 --> 1:02:41.730
What?

1:02:41.796 --> 1:02:43.768
Can I ask what's happening?

1:02:43.834 --> 1:02:46.507
Bill?

1:02:46.573 --> 1:02:47.508
Bill.

1:02:49.612 --> 1:02:51.448
Bill, what are you doing?

1:02:51.516 --> 1:02:53.419
What are you looking for,
a sign from God?

1:02:53.486 --> 1:02:56.358
Some sort of pioneer trek
into the desert?

1:02:57.862 --> 1:02:59.599
Hello.

1:02:59.665 --> 1:03:00.834
Bill!

1:03:05.477 --> 1:03:07.649
What the fuck?

1:03:07.715 --> 1:03:09.051
[echoing]
What the fuck?

1:03:19.505 --> 1:03:21.810
- Just take a moment.

1:03:21.876 --> 1:03:23.245
Look out.

1:03:27.086 --> 1:03:29.258
I'm not sure why folks
need to call such things

1:03:29.325 --> 1:03:31.062
a sign from God.

1:03:31.128 --> 1:03:34.134
Why not just appreciate it?

1:03:39.779 --> 1:03:41.817
If there is no God,

1:03:41.883 --> 1:03:44.956
isn't this just
all the more miraculous?

1:03:51.937 --> 1:03:54.274
- [grunts] Oh!

1:03:54.341 --> 1:03:56.045
[coughs]

1:03:56.112 --> 1:03:58.416
- Breathe...
- [panting] What?

1:03:58.483 --> 1:04:01.188
- From here.

1:04:01.255 --> 1:04:05.229
What I'm saying is,
be here and listen.

1:04:06.566 --> 1:04:09.907
The gut is wiser
than most people think.

1:04:09.973 --> 1:04:12.812
It's a compass.

1:04:12.879 --> 1:04:14.749
It'll give you
all the wisdom you need.

1:04:14.816 --> 1:04:21.896
♪♪ ♪♪

1:04:32.918 --> 1:04:35.056
- Dan was in a dream I had.

1:04:37.929 --> 1:04:41.002
He said, "I am His One."

1:04:41.068 --> 1:04:42.370
- Oh, Jesus fucking Christ.

1:04:42.437 --> 1:04:44.008
Enough with
the Holy Spirit shit, Jeb.

1:04:44.074 --> 1:04:46.245
- For better or for worse,
this is my gut.

1:04:46.312 --> 1:04:48.249
The dream was born out of--
out of Dan's journals.

1:04:48.316 --> 1:04:50.354
It was Allen's history books.

1:04:50.420 --> 1:04:52.992
Every single Sunday school
I ever had to sit through,

1:04:53.058 --> 1:04:56.265
and he said One, not two.

1:04:56.332 --> 1:04:58.269
- So Dan whispered "One"
in a dream.

1:04:58.335 --> 1:05:00.373
- This goes well beyond Dan.

1:05:00.439 --> 1:05:02.978
After the Mormons
massacred that wagon train,

1:05:03.045 --> 1:05:05.216
U.S. troops started
to advance on Utah,

1:05:05.283 --> 1:05:08.758
and they--they came
to arrest Brigham...

1:05:08.824 --> 1:05:09.859
PERSON: Joseph.

1:05:09.926 --> 1:05:12.898
- To seize all church assets,

1:05:12.965 --> 1:05:15.169
and to end polygamy.

1:05:16.606 --> 1:05:18.476
And it was very clear
to our third prophet

1:05:18.543 --> 1:05:19.779
that the church
was in real trouble,

1:05:19.846 --> 1:05:21.817
that the--that the church's
days were numbered,

1:05:21.883 --> 1:05:23.452
so he made a calculation.

1:05:23.520 --> 1:05:26.125
JOHN: We must beat the devil
at his own game.

1:05:26.192 --> 1:05:27.728
JEB:
He gathered the saints.

1:05:27.795 --> 1:05:30.400
- We must deceive the Gentiles
into believing

1:05:30.466 --> 1:05:32.605
that we have disavowed
His holy principle.

1:05:32.672 --> 1:05:34.475
JEB:
The principle of polygamy

1:05:34.542 --> 1:05:36.646
had to be kept alive
but in private.

1:05:36.713 --> 1:05:39.585
He invoked the words of our
first prophet, Joseph Smith.

1:05:39.652 --> 1:05:42.491
- I will send
One Mighty and Strong...

1:05:42.558 --> 1:05:44.528
- And he said
One Mighty and Strong.

1:05:44.595 --> 1:05:47.201
"One day, One Mighty and Strong
will come"...

1:05:47.267 --> 1:05:49.506
- Holding the scepter of power
in his hand

1:05:49.572 --> 1:05:52.043
to set in order
the house of God.

1:05:52.110 --> 1:05:54.415
- And that seed,
pushed into the earth,

1:05:54.482 --> 1:05:57.756
has set the likes
of Onias and Brady

1:05:57.822 --> 1:06:02.632
and Dan and Ron and countless
other men for generations

1:06:02.699 --> 1:06:06.338
on quests to prove
that they are God's One.

1:06:06.405 --> 1:06:08.677
And it's One.
It is not two.

1:06:08.744 --> 1:06:11.181
There were two brothers
in that casino.

1:06:11.248 --> 1:06:12.918
They both got down
on their knees.

1:06:12.985 --> 1:06:14.288
They both know every rule,

1:06:14.355 --> 1:06:16.292
so with that win
began a new struggle

1:06:16.359 --> 1:06:18.363
for that singular seat.

1:06:18.429 --> 1:06:21.135
A singular seat
next to Heavenly Father.

1:06:21.202 --> 1:06:23.574
The pretender...

1:06:23.641 --> 1:06:24.976
must be eliminated

1:06:25.043 --> 1:06:27.414
if their list
is to remain holy.

1:06:27.481 --> 1:06:31.455
One must end the other before
they set forth to kill again.

1:06:32.725 --> 1:06:35.831
- It's a colorful theory
based on scripture.

1:06:35.897 --> 1:06:37.501
- Scripture is their facts.

1:06:37.568 --> 1:06:41.308
So if you're asking my gut,
right here, right now,

1:06:41.375 --> 1:06:43.279
we call Reno's morgues.

1:06:43.346 --> 1:06:45.350
And if they don't
have Dan or Ron on ice,

1:06:45.416 --> 1:06:46.619
we turn around,
we head back,

1:06:46.686 --> 1:06:49.826
'cause both brothers
cannot leave Reno alive.

1:06:49.892 --> 1:06:51.630
There can only be one.

1:06:51.696 --> 1:06:53.867
[panting]

1:06:53.934 --> 1:06:56.906
[tense music]

1:06:56.973 --> 1:06:58.610
♪♪ ♪♪

1:06:58.677 --> 1:07:01.649
[birds chirping]

1:07:01.716 --> 1:07:08.597
♪♪ ♪♪

1:07:59.398 --> 1:08:00.534
[floorboards creak]

1:08:00.601 --> 1:08:01.669
[footsteps thud]

1:08:04.007 --> 1:08:04.875
- [whispering]
"We must stand up

1:08:04.942 --> 1:08:06.111
to those who lead us astray"...

1:08:06.178 --> 1:08:07.848
[floorboard creaks]

1:08:07.915 --> 1:08:11.656
♪♪ ♪♪

1:08:11.722 --> 1:08:15.396
"We must stand up
to those who lead us astray

1:08:15.463 --> 1:08:17.668
"so we may stand glorified
on the last day,

1:08:17.735 --> 1:08:20.540
with you, my eternal sister,
by my side."

1:08:23.514 --> 1:08:25.016
RENO COP:
The only unidentified body

1:08:25.083 --> 1:08:27.087
in any morgue in town
is female.

1:08:27.153 --> 1:08:28.857
There's no Ron
or Dan Lafferty here.

1:08:28.924 --> 1:08:30.628
JEB: Okay, so call
every other casino.

1:08:30.694 --> 1:08:31.630
It's lunchtime.

1:08:31.696 --> 1:08:33.232
I need eyes
on every single buffet.

1:08:33.299 --> 1:08:35.937
Who knows how many other Sandys
they've married?

1:08:36.004 --> 1:08:37.875
Please.
Thank you.

1:08:37.942 --> 1:08:42.518
♪♪ ♪♪

1:08:42.585 --> 1:08:44.487
BILL: All right.
I got you, buddy.

1:08:46.526 --> 1:08:48.296
- Hey. Bill. Bill.
BILL: Yeah?

1:08:48.362 --> 1:08:49.699
JEB:
That looks like Dan to me.

1:08:49.766 --> 1:08:51.937
BILL:
Yeah, so where's Ron?

1:08:52.004 --> 1:08:54.909
[suspenseful music]

1:08:54.976 --> 1:09:01.923
♪♪ ♪♪

1:09:08.135 --> 1:09:09.605
[iron sizzles]

1:09:20.126 --> 1:09:27.206
♪♪ ♪♪

1:09:40.233 --> 1:09:43.205
[tense music]

1:09:43.272 --> 1:09:50.386
♪♪ ♪♪

1:09:55.664 --> 1:09:56.600
JEB: All right.
That's not normal.

1:09:56.666 --> 1:09:57.668
Is it?
RENO COP: No.

1:09:57.735 --> 1:09:58.970
- We need to shut
this casino down

1:09:59.037 --> 1:10:01.408
quietly and immediately.

1:10:03.914 --> 1:10:05.717
- Get me FBI now.

1:10:05.784 --> 1:10:07.153
- What's back there?
What--what's beyond?

1:10:07.220 --> 1:10:08.723
What's beyond that--
that hallway?

1:10:08.790 --> 1:10:11.161
Do we have cameras on--
beyond that hallway?

1:10:11.228 --> 1:10:12.865
OFFICER 1: No, Sir.
OFFICER 2: No.

1:10:14.468 --> 1:10:21.616
♪♪ ♪♪

1:10:30.466 --> 1:10:32.303
[thud]
[Dianna grunts]

1:10:32.370 --> 1:10:33.774
MATILDA: Die!
DIANNA: No, Matilda!

1:10:33.841 --> 1:10:34.942
No, no!

1:10:35.009 --> 1:10:36.111
It's me.

1:10:36.178 --> 1:10:38.015
No. Matilda.

1:10:38.082 --> 1:10:39.150
DAN: I will go anywhere!

1:10:39.217 --> 1:10:40.520
I will do anything...
DIANNA: It's me.

1:10:40.587 --> 1:10:41.556
DAN: And go anywhere!

1:10:41.623 --> 1:10:43.425
I feel it, Lord!
Yes!

1:10:44.762 --> 1:10:46.298
- It's me.

1:10:46.365 --> 1:10:48.970
It's me.
[breathing heavily]

1:10:49.037 --> 1:10:51.241
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
DIANNA: It's okay. No, Matilda.

1:10:51.308 --> 1:10:53.980
It's okay, Matilda.

1:10:57.487 --> 1:10:59.324
Are Ron and Dan in the house?

1:10:59.391 --> 1:11:01.563
- Um...

1:11:01.630 --> 1:11:03.734
uh, Dan, uh, called yesterday,

1:11:03.801 --> 1:11:06.038
and he said
he's coming back for me.

1:11:06.105 --> 1:11:08.275
- We have to leave.

1:11:08.342 --> 1:11:10.213
Right now.
- No, I can't leave, Dianna.

1:11:10.279 --> 1:11:11.716
They'll come and kill me.

1:11:13.921 --> 1:11:17.928
- If you stay here,
the same thing will happen.

1:11:17.995 --> 1:11:20.634
Matilda,
if we don't leave right now,

1:11:20.701 --> 1:11:23.005
you'll never see
your girls again.

1:11:23.072 --> 1:11:25.076
- Dan says
they're gone forever, Dianna.

1:11:25.143 --> 1:11:27.548
- He's lying to you.

1:11:27.615 --> 1:11:30.286
I promise you,
he's lying.

1:11:30.353 --> 1:11:32.558
Come with me.
Come with me.

1:11:32.625 --> 1:11:34.027
DOREEN:
Matilda!

1:11:36.633 --> 1:11:38.302
BILL:
Guessing she's not handicapped.

1:11:38.369 --> 1:11:40.774
- No, and she's just
locked in the spot

1:11:40.840 --> 1:11:42.711
closest to the back door.
OFFICER: She's back.

1:11:42.778 --> 1:11:44.080
- Dan Lafferty's
back there right now.

1:11:44.147 --> 1:11:45.617
FBI AGENT:
Get your team to the back lot.

1:11:45.684 --> 1:11:47.989
If necessary,
we neutralize him.

1:11:48.055 --> 1:11:49.357
Let's go!

1:11:49.424 --> 1:11:51.696
- We try to take them alive
if possible.

1:11:51.763 --> 1:11:53.566
They sliced the mother's throat
from ear to ear.

1:11:53.633 --> 1:11:55.336
They did the same
to her baby girl.

1:11:55.403 --> 1:11:57.608
If one drop of their blood
hits the ground,

1:11:57.675 --> 1:11:59.945
they die thinking
this is all God's plan.

1:12:00.012 --> 1:12:06.926
♪♪ ♪♪

1:12:08.563 --> 1:12:09.498
DIANNA:
It's locked.

1:12:09.565 --> 1:12:10.634
MATILDA:
Only Mother has the key.

1:12:10.701 --> 1:12:11.802
DOREEN:
Dianna?

1:12:14.108 --> 1:12:15.544
Okay, just stay.

1:12:15.610 --> 1:12:16.980
You stay right there.

1:12:17.047 --> 1:12:21.222
♪♪ ♪♪

1:12:21.288 --> 1:12:23.192
It's not a woman's place
to resist.

1:12:23.258 --> 1:12:26.265
[dramatic music]

1:12:26.331 --> 1:12:27.835
You can abandon Zion,

1:12:27.902 --> 1:12:30.373
but you'll never escape
His wrath!

1:12:30.440 --> 1:12:35.282
♪♪ ♪♪

1:12:35.349 --> 1:12:38.455
[indistinct chatter]

1:12:40.059 --> 1:12:41.261
DANCER:
Oh!

1:12:41.328 --> 1:12:44.234
[tense music]

1:12:44.301 --> 1:12:50.814
♪♪ ♪♪

1:12:50.881 --> 1:12:53.385
- Sandy, right?
Detective Taba.

1:12:53.452 --> 1:12:55.155
Come with me, please.
- What's wrong?

1:12:55.222 --> 1:12:57.326
- Just come with me.
- What's happening?

1:12:57.393 --> 1:12:59.297
Excuse me.
What's happening?

1:12:59.364 --> 1:13:00.299
[door bangs open]

1:13:00.366 --> 1:13:03.005
[dancers gasp]

1:13:03.072 --> 1:13:04.141
JEB:
Okay.

1:13:04.208 --> 1:13:05.142
Move, move.

1:13:05.209 --> 1:13:12.156
♪♪ ♪♪

1:13:24.849 --> 1:13:26.218
DIANNA:
Okay, you stay down.

1:13:26.284 --> 1:13:28.021
Don't let anyone see you.

1:13:28.088 --> 1:13:35.035
♪♪ ♪♪

1:13:47.093 --> 1:13:48.730
JEB: Come on!
Come on! Move!

1:13:48.797 --> 1:13:50.834
Move! Move! Move! Move! Move!

1:13:50.901 --> 1:13:52.437
OFFICER:
Need one back here, guys!

1:13:52.505 --> 1:13:55.711
♪♪ ♪♪

1:13:55.777 --> 1:13:57.113
[indistinct shouting]

1:13:57.180 --> 1:14:00.052
BILL: So why did you move
your car closer to the door?

1:14:00.119 --> 1:14:01.956
- I thought
I was gonna get sick,

1:14:02.023 --> 1:14:05.163
so I moved the car
in case I needed to lay down.

1:14:05.229 --> 1:14:07.634
I, um--I think I'm pregnant.

1:14:11.108 --> 1:14:12.645
PERFORMER: Oh!
OFFICER: Sit down!

1:14:12.712 --> 1:14:15.015
PERFORMER:
Hey. Hey.

1:14:15.082 --> 1:14:18.590
JEB: Nothing?
OFFICER: They're not here.

1:14:18.656 --> 1:14:20.426
JEB:
Police! Freeze!

1:14:20.493 --> 1:14:22.597
Relax. Just relax.
Everyone relax.

1:14:22.664 --> 1:14:24.902
Stay calm.

1:14:24.969 --> 1:14:26.806
FBI AGENT: All clear.
Dressing rooms are all clear.

1:14:26.872 --> 1:14:28.944
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

1:14:29.011 --> 1:14:30.580
I've got nothing in here, sir.

1:14:40.734 --> 1:14:43.205
SAM:
Hey!

1:14:43.272 --> 1:14:44.575
Mom called.

1:14:44.642 --> 1:14:46.077
Said you invaded our home,

1:14:46.144 --> 1:14:47.815
stole my brother's property.
DIANNA: No, no, no, no, no.

1:14:47.882 --> 1:14:48.950
SAM: Out of the car, woman.
DIANNA: No, no, no.

1:14:49.017 --> 1:14:51.187
No, no, no.
Sam, please don't hurt her.

1:14:51.254 --> 1:14:52.691
Please help.
Stop him.

1:14:52.758 --> 1:14:54.194
Please help her.
He's gonna hurt her.

1:14:54.261 --> 1:14:56.065
Help her!
- Gotta keep our girls in line.

1:14:56.131 --> 1:14:58.503
- He's gonna hurt her!
Someone help her!

1:14:58.570 --> 1:15:04.381
♪♪ ♪♪

1:15:04.447 --> 1:15:07.387
Bear your testimony, Sam!

1:15:07.453 --> 1:15:08.991
Do you step on women's necks

1:15:09.057 --> 1:15:11.461
because
it makes you feel taller?

1:15:11.529 --> 1:15:14.669
Because your mother told you
you were a chosen one?

1:15:14.735 --> 1:15:18.175
That our country
is to blame for your failings?

1:15:19.779 --> 1:15:22.517
Well, it's a lie!

1:15:22.584 --> 1:15:24.454
You are not special!

1:15:24.522 --> 1:15:25.924
You are not chosen!

1:15:25.990 --> 1:15:28.830
You and your brothers
simply failed!

1:15:30.500 --> 1:15:35.043
You are a small, weak

1:15:35.109 --> 1:15:38.449
child of a man.

1:15:38.517 --> 1:15:40.019
This I know to be true.

1:15:40.086 --> 1:15:43.058
♪♪ ♪♪

1:15:43.125 --> 1:15:46.632
You show him how weak he is,
Matilda.

1:15:48.168 --> 1:15:49.337
Show him!

1:15:50.907 --> 1:15:53.579
Go on.
Show him now.

1:15:53.646 --> 1:15:55.216
Yes. Okay.

1:15:55.283 --> 1:15:57.320
Okay, come here.

1:15:57.386 --> 1:15:58.690
Sara.

1:15:58.757 --> 1:15:59.959
Sara, come with us!

1:16:00.026 --> 1:16:02.396
You don't have
to stay with him.

1:16:02.463 --> 1:16:04.334
Come with us. Come.

1:16:04.401 --> 1:16:11.014
♪♪ ♪♪

1:16:11.081 --> 1:16:13.720
Get in the frickin' car,
Matilda.

1:16:13.787 --> 1:16:20.900
♪♪ ♪♪

1:16:26.979 --> 1:16:29.083
Shame on all of you!

1:16:31.856 --> 1:16:34.762
[dramatic music]

1:16:34.829 --> 1:16:41.743
♪♪ ♪♪

1:16:41.809 --> 1:16:43.345
[stall door clatters]

1:16:48.355 --> 1:16:49.357
- Dan.

1:16:52.029 --> 1:16:53.866
I've received
another revelation.

1:16:56.506 --> 1:16:58.976
It has been revealed to me
that you're a false prophet,

1:16:59.043 --> 1:17:01.081
and that in order
for His will to be done,

1:17:01.148 --> 1:17:03.084
you must perish.

1:17:14.307 --> 1:17:17.681
- So you're going
to blood atone me, then?

1:17:17.748 --> 1:17:19.151
RON:
No, Brother.

1:17:19.217 --> 1:17:21.154
'Cause your deceptions
are so wicked,

1:17:21.221 --> 1:17:23.158
you shall not see
your blood spill.

1:17:32.811 --> 1:17:34.848
You shall not enter
the kingdom of heaven.

1:17:34.915 --> 1:17:41.962
♪♪ ♪♪

1:17:46.539 --> 1:17:48.475
- How about we pray on it, Ron?

1:17:48.542 --> 1:17:50.245
Together.

1:17:50.312 --> 1:17:52.350
I think we should pray on it,
don't you?

1:17:52.417 --> 1:17:55.289
[tense music]

1:17:55.356 --> 1:18:00.332
♪♪ ♪♪

1:18:00.399 --> 1:18:02.169
Dear Heavenly Father...

1:18:02.236 --> 1:18:04.440
♪♪ ♪♪

1:18:04.508 --> 1:18:05.844
- [panting]
All right.

1:18:05.911 --> 1:18:11.321
♪♪ ♪♪

1:18:11.388 --> 1:18:14.360
[sports announcer speaking
indistinctly over radio]

1:18:16.064 --> 1:18:17.400
Anyone else
come through here?

1:18:17.467 --> 1:18:20.807
CUSTODIAN: People come
through here all the time.

1:18:20.874 --> 1:18:24.180
- I ask You that
You may create a path for me

1:18:24.247 --> 1:18:28.723
to be a vessel for You and...

1:18:28.790 --> 1:18:30.092
a vessel for You through Ron,

1:18:30.159 --> 1:18:32.898
and I will accept
anything that You--

1:18:32.965 --> 1:18:34.702
[clattering]

1:18:34.768 --> 1:18:37.473
[both grunting]

1:18:37.541 --> 1:18:40.479
[eerie music]

1:18:40.547 --> 1:18:41.615
♪♪ ♪♪

1:18:41.682 --> 1:18:44.120
[Dan gagging]

1:18:45.590 --> 1:18:49.163
Shed my blood, Brother!

1:18:49.230 --> 1:18:52.337
[grunting]

1:18:52.403 --> 1:18:53.907
[choking]

1:18:53.973 --> 1:18:55.376
RON:
Stop it!

1:18:55.442 --> 1:18:57.380
Stop resisting!

1:18:57.447 --> 1:19:00.185
[breathing frantically]

1:19:06.632 --> 1:19:08.936
JEB:
In here! In here!

1:19:09.003 --> 1:19:11.408
No!
No, no, no, no, no!

1:19:11.474 --> 1:19:14.380
[both grunting]

1:19:14.447 --> 1:19:21.361
♪♪ ♪♪

1:19:27.473 --> 1:19:29.377
[Dan gasps, coughs]

1:19:29.444 --> 1:19:31.114
[Ron exclaims]

1:19:31.181 --> 1:19:32.718
- Heavenly Father...
RON: You heathen!

1:19:32.784 --> 1:19:35.957
[wailing]

1:19:39.163 --> 1:19:41.769
- Oh, Father,
where are You?

1:19:41.836 --> 1:19:43.171
- Grab him!

1:19:51.756 --> 1:19:54.695
[somber music]

1:19:54.762 --> 1:19:57.767
♪♪ ♪♪

1:19:57.834 --> 1:20:00.973
[indistinct chatter]

1:20:02.544 --> 1:20:05.550
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

1:20:07.486 --> 1:20:09.190
- Forgive them, Dan,

1:20:09.257 --> 1:20:12.530
for they know not
what they do.

1:20:12.597 --> 1:20:14.668
Dan.

1:20:14.735 --> 1:20:15.903
Dan?

1:20:18.408 --> 1:20:20.847
[weakly]
Dan?

1:20:20.914 --> 1:20:26.424
♪♪ ♪♪

1:20:26.491 --> 1:20:28.496
- I ask you,

1:20:28.563 --> 1:20:30.867
was Abraham a criminal?

1:20:30.934 --> 1:20:32.470
Or Brigham Young?

1:20:32.538 --> 1:20:34.942
♪♪ ♪♪

1:20:35.009 --> 1:20:37.346
What laws of heaven

1:20:37.413 --> 1:20:39.317
have I broken?

1:20:39.383 --> 1:20:40.319
None!

1:20:40.386 --> 1:20:46.599
♪♪ ♪♪

1:20:46.666 --> 1:20:48.369
I am Elijah.

1:20:48.435 --> 1:20:51.474
[siren wailing]

1:20:51.542 --> 1:20:55.517
♪♪ ♪♪

1:20:55.583 --> 1:20:58.222
- What is that?

1:20:58.288 --> 1:20:59.658
- It's the state line.

1:20:59.725 --> 1:21:06.638
♪♪ ♪♪

1:21:20.700 --> 1:21:22.069
MATILDA:
Thank you.

1:21:33.927 --> 1:21:35.362
BILL: Hey.
JEB: Hey.

1:21:35.429 --> 1:21:37.166
Gonna see
if I can get a flight back

1:21:37.232 --> 1:21:39.371
to Salt Lake or Miami.

1:21:39.437 --> 1:21:41.575
BILL: Salt Lake.
Morris checked in.

1:21:41.642 --> 1:21:43.311
Dianna called her kids
back in Florida

1:21:43.378 --> 1:21:45.683
from a gas station
just over the Utah border.

1:21:45.750 --> 1:21:47.052
Matilda's with her.

1:21:47.119 --> 1:21:48.221
They're safe.

1:21:48.288 --> 1:21:49.858
- Better call Allen.

1:21:49.925 --> 1:21:51.227
BILL:
Allen knows.

1:21:51.294 --> 1:21:52.564
Betty picked him up.

1:21:52.631 --> 1:21:54.935
He's in Idaho now
with Brenda's folks.

1:21:55.001 --> 1:21:57.039
- With her Bishop dad?

1:21:57.105 --> 1:21:59.644
- If it's what he needs,
let him have it, Jeb.

1:21:59.711 --> 1:22:01.280
Go home.

1:22:06.992 --> 1:22:09.396
Angel of God,
guardian dear,

1:22:09.463 --> 1:22:12.169
to whom His love
commits me here.

1:22:12.236 --> 1:22:14.942
Ever this day,
be at my side

1:22:15.009 --> 1:22:17.112
to light and guard,
to rule and guide.

1:22:18.950 --> 1:22:20.553
Had to learn
that whole Catholic thing

1:22:20.620 --> 1:22:22.156
when my folks converted.

1:22:22.223 --> 1:22:24.528
- Oh. [laughs]
- Never shook that one.

1:22:24.595 --> 1:22:27.000
[both laugh]

1:22:27.066 --> 1:22:28.837
How 'bout this?

1:22:28.903 --> 1:22:30.372
Dear Heavenly Father,

1:22:30.439 --> 1:22:33.680
bless Jeb's return home
to his family

1:22:33.747 --> 1:22:36.284
and my return to TV dinners,
midnight Marlboros,

1:22:36.351 --> 1:22:39.190
and endless Diet Cokes.

1:22:39.257 --> 1:22:41.294
In the name of Jesus Christ,
amen.

1:22:44.334 --> 1:22:45.804
JEB: Yeah...
BILL: Your last try.

1:22:45.870 --> 1:22:47.339
JEB: [laughs]
Oh, gosh.

1:22:47.406 --> 1:22:48.375
BILL: You know,
when the colonists

1:22:48.442 --> 1:22:50.212
were wiping out my ancestors,

1:22:50.278 --> 1:22:51.949
we received a prayer of hope

1:22:52.016 --> 1:22:54.053
that one day,
they'd all vanish

1:22:54.120 --> 1:22:56.057
and the buffalo would return.

1:22:57.928 --> 1:23:00.833
[singing in Paiute]

1:23:00.900 --> 1:23:08.047
♪♪ ♪♪

1:23:18.669 --> 1:23:20.840
- You think
that holds some power?

1:23:20.907 --> 1:23:22.243
- Nope.

1:23:22.309 --> 1:23:23.579
When the white man
saw us singing it,

1:23:23.646 --> 1:23:25.816
they just mowed us down
like blades of grass

1:23:25.883 --> 1:23:27.319
with their Christ-sickles.

1:23:29.089 --> 1:23:31.795
I like singing it anyhow.

1:23:31.862 --> 1:23:33.766
Reminds me of home.

1:23:33.833 --> 1:23:35.536
We all need a home, Jeb,

1:23:35.603 --> 1:23:38.742
so I think it's okay
to sing it now and then

1:23:38.809 --> 1:23:41.915
even if I don't believe
it has power anymore.

1:23:41.982 --> 1:23:49.063
♪♪ ♪♪

1:23:52.236 --> 1:23:53.404
JEB:
Hi there.

1:23:55.342 --> 1:23:58.650
- It's time to put this one
in the drawer, Jeb.

1:23:58.716 --> 1:24:00.118
Good job.

1:24:07.568 --> 1:24:08.535
- Thank you.

1:24:10.339 --> 1:24:11.642
[sighs]
How are you doing?

1:24:14.180 --> 1:24:17.019
[melancholy piano music
playing]

1:24:17.086 --> 1:24:24.233
♪♪ ♪♪

1:24:46.845 --> 1:24:47.814
- Annie.
[music stops]

1:24:47.881 --> 1:24:49.149
ANNIE:
Daddy.

1:24:51.221 --> 1:24:53.960
- [chuckles]

1:24:54.027 --> 1:24:56.798
CAROLINE: Daddy!
JEB: Trouble! Aw!

1:25:00.773 --> 1:25:01.709
- Hi.

1:25:01.775 --> 1:25:03.178
- Hey.

1:25:03.245 --> 1:25:04.781
Hey.
- Hey.

1:25:04.848 --> 1:25:07.754
[somber music]

1:25:07.821 --> 1:25:14.768
♪♪ ♪♪

1:25:16.638 --> 1:25:17.874
Hey.

1:25:17.941 --> 1:25:24.888
♪♪ ♪♪

1:25:27.159 --> 1:25:29.197
- So who's gonna
do the honors?

1:25:29.263 --> 1:25:31.101
Caroline?
- Yes, please!

1:25:31.167 --> 1:25:32.336
JEB:
Okay, go ahead.

1:25:35.042 --> 1:25:37.046
CAROLINE:
Dear Heavenly Father,

1:25:37.112 --> 1:25:38.883
thank You
for bringing Daddy home

1:25:38.950 --> 1:25:41.020
and our family back together.

1:25:41.087 --> 1:25:48.201
♪♪ ♪♪

1:26:05.670 --> 1:26:08.474
[birds chirping]

1:26:08.542 --> 1:26:11.648
[dramatic orchestral music]

1:26:11.715 --> 1:26:18.629
♪♪ ♪♪

1:26:19.832 --> 1:26:24.440
- Oh, it's just a gift
from our Heavenly Father.

1:26:26.043 --> 1:26:27.680
It's a miracle.

1:26:27.747 --> 1:26:34.694
♪♪ ♪♪

1:26:36.264 --> 1:26:38.569
- Or just to be here
with you, Mom.

1:26:41.908 --> 1:26:44.279
I think that may be
miracle enough for me.

1:26:45.716 --> 1:26:47.319
Is that okay, Mom?
- Yes.

1:26:47.386 --> 1:26:49.958
Oh, my God, yes.

1:26:50.025 --> 1:26:56.938
♪♪ ♪♪
